{"type":"message","id":"7bcb9ad3","parentId":"bf1cd660","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:04:04.771Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n\n1. `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json` is from the web-based tzzb (tzzb.10jqka.com.cn) and it was generated on 2026-04-01, which is 13 days old. The overlay system checks it for staleness and refuses to use it because it's older than 24 hours.\n\n2. The user is saying they gave me a Tushare token yesterday (April 13), and wants me to use the Tushare data source instead of the stale web source.\n\n3. The `ths_local_holdings_selection.json` config says `selected_ledger_ids: []` which means it's using `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json` as the primary source (web-based), not local THS app data.\n   \nI see there's actually a local THS holdings skill available that can inspect holdings from both the web tzzb app and the local macOS app—it's just not being leveraged here. The real issue is that the system needs to either fetch fresh data or fall back to the local app source instead of relying on the stale web snapshot.\n\nThe overlay system is checking the web source's age and rejecting anything over 24 hours old, so I need to either regenerate that data today or find where that staleness check is happening and bypass it. Let me trace through the overlay skill to see what it's actually trying to do and where the failure occurs.\n","thinkingSignature":"62d3eff6a140b77716421c51419f3c9eb2d552bd80d55a755315e99d77be019a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nwru9fv08hhy_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/web_source_fusion_daily_latest.json 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nwru9fv08hhy_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/skills/a-share-fusion-report/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":231,"output":397,"cacheRead":65408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66036,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776132229410,"responseId":"062cd3860c5ec1b809b1a0db08cc6c8d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bde7de87","parentId":"7bcb9ad3","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:04:05.011Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nwru9fv08hhy_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"FAILED_CLOSED\",\n  \"input_file\": \"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json\",\n  \"output_dir\": \"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports\",\n  \"checked_at\": \"2026-04-14 09:25:40\",\n  \"reason\": \"stale_web_source_latest\",\n  \"source_generated_at\": \"2026-04-01 16:37:49\",\n  \"max_age_hours\": 24.0\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":82,"aggregated":"{\n  \"status\": \"FAILED_CLOSED\",\n  \"input_file\": \"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json\",\n  \"output_dir\": \"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports\",\n  \"checked_at\": \"2026-04-14 09:25:40\",\n  \"reason\": \"stale_web_source_latest\",\n  \"source_generated_at\": \"2026-04-01 16:37:49\",\n  \"max_age_hours\": 24.0\n}","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776132244970}}
{"type":"message","id":"520ca106","parentId":"bde7de87","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:04:05.015Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nwru9fv08hhy_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: a-share-fusion-report\ndescription: \"Generate a unified A-share report by combining three installed skills: stock-daily-report (HTML/PNG professional report), stock-watcher (fast structured quote fallback), and akshare-stock (fund-flow overlay). Use when you need one reliable daily report from current holdings, automatic fallback if one data source fails, and optional Feishu push (especially for trading-day 09:25 automation).\"\n---\n\n# A-Share Fusion Report\n\nRun this skill when you want one consolidated output instead of manually running multiple stock skills.\n\n## What this skill does\n\n1. Loads holdings codes from one source, in order of priority:\n   - explicit `--input-file` (`json/csv/xlsx/xls/txt`)\n   - explicit `--codes`\n   - autodiscovery from latest portfolio source:\n     - `quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/ths_web_holding_count_fix_*.json`\n     - fallback: `.../ths_app_holdings_*.csv`\n2. Centralizes input parsing, validation, and input snapshots.\n3. Syncs watchlists to both engines:\n   - `workspace/skills/stock-daily-report/config.json`\n   - `~/.clawdbot/stock_watcher/watchlist.txt`\n4. Generates a professional report via `stock-daily-report`.\n5. Adds fallback quote lines from `stock-watcher`.\n6. Adds `akshare-stock` fund-flow overlay (top-N symbols).\n7. Writes stable artifacts for each run and updates latest pointers.\n\n## Commands\n\n### A) Fast local test with inline codes\n\n```bash\npython3 skills/a-share-fusion-report/scripts/run_fusion_report.py --codes 600519,000001 --limit 2\n```\n\n### B) Run from explicit holdings Excel\n\n```bash\npython3 skills/a-share-fusion-report/scripts/run_fusion_report.py \\\n  --input-file ~/.openclaw/media/inbound/shares---a2a3de8e-91a6-41a7-b3a4-0e928661a43e.xlsx \\\n  --limit 5\n```\n\n### C) Full holdings run + Feishu push\n\n```bash\npython3 skills/a-share-fusion-report/scripts/run_fusion_report.py --push-feishu\n```\n\n### D) Trading-day only guard\n\n```bash\npython3 skills/a-share-fusion-report/scripts/run_fusion_report.py --trading-day-only --push-feishu\n```\n\n### E) Fail-closed example (no 6-digit A-share codes)\n\n```bash\npython3 skills/a-share-fusion-report/scripts/run_fusion_report.py --codes 2188,2316\n```\n\n### F) Install 09:25 weekday cron\n\n```bash\nbash skills/a-share-fusion-report/scripts/install_cron_0925.sh\n```\n\n## Key output\n\nDefault output directory:\n`quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports`\n\nPer-run stable artifacts:\n- `a-share-fusion-report_runs/<RUN_ID>/input_snapshot.json`\n- `a-share-fusion-report_runs/<RUN_ID>/input_snapshot.csv`\n- `a-share-fusion-report_runs/<RUN_ID>/summary.json`\n- `a-share-fusion-report_runs/<RUN_ID>/report.md`\n- `a-share-fusion-report_runs/<RUN_ID>/run_summary.txt`\n\nLatest stable pointers:\n- `a-share-fusion-report_latest_input_snapshot.json`\n- `a-share-fusion-report_latest_input_snapshot.csv`\n- `a-share-fusion-report_latest_summary.json`\n- `a-share-fusion-report_latest.md`\n- `a-share-fusion-report_latest_run_summary.txt`\n\nCompatibility outputs retained:\n- `a-share-fusion-report_<RUN_ID>.md`\n- `a-share-fusion-report_<RUN_ID>.json`\n- plus `stock-daily-report_<RUN_ID>.html/.png` when available\n\n## Fail-closed rules\n\nThe script stops with non-zero exit when:\n- no holdings source can be found\n- the input file is missing / unsupported / schema-unreadable\n- no normalized stock codes can be extracted\n- no 6-digit A-share codes remain after parsing\n- `stock-daily-report` and `stock-watcher` both fail in the same run\n\n## Notes\n\n- Non-6-digit codes (e.g. HK) are preserved in input snapshots and run metadata, but only 6-digit A-share symbols are sent to A-share engines.\n- `stock-daily-report` is treated as a preferred engine, not the only engine: if it fails but `stock-watcher` succeeds, the run is marked `SUCCESS_WITH_FALLBACK`.\n- `akshare-stock` overlay is best-effort; partial failures are captured in the run summary instead of silently dropped.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776132245011}}
{"type":"message","id":"3b20c3a7","parentId":"520ca106","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:04:25.247Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the architecture. The `a-share-fusion-report` skill runs on the `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json` file, which is the holdings data fetched from the THS web API. The `web_source_fusion_daily_latest.json` runner JSON tracks the status of this process, and it FAILED_CLOSED because the source file `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json` is from April 1 (stale - more than 24 hours old).\n\nThe core issue is that the daily scheduled task that should fetch fresh holdings from the THS web API is not running or not updating the source file. The Tushare token IS configured in `/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/.env` but the overlay system seems to need the THS web API which was \"接通\" (connected) this morning.\n\n\nI need to check how the overlay system retrieves holdings data from the THS web API to understand where the scheduled task is breaking down.\n","thinkingSignature":"970d73bd2afa56e05c8652839f530ef77183a9e15d58b58e7978fc78e3e466e2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v8cyr3vzfbmc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/ -name \"*.py\" | xargs grep -l \"ths_web_selected\\|tzzb\\|stock_position\\|web_holding\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".pyc\\|test\\|__pycache__\" | head -15"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v8cyr3vzfbmc_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/ -name \"*.py\" -newer /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json 2>/dev/null | xargs grep -l \"ths_selected_holdings\\|ths_web_selected\\|generate_live\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".pyc\\|test\" | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"inpu