{"type":"message","id":"0102d30a","parentId":"426759fe","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:06:40.229Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the issue clearly. The Tushare Token is:\n1. Set in `/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/.env` with value `e3d8c68a414b9a84cbc49c637ec00875c7173a961eba98cff09c1afc`\n2. The `daily_stock_analysis_upgrade_preview` project reads it from environment variable `TUSHARE_TOKEN`\n3. But when running via the overlay cron, the environment variable is NOT loaded from `.env`, so `config.tushare_token` is `None`\n\n\n4. The system uses THS Level2 (Tonghua Xun) which is already prioritized in the config, but the SSL certificate issue prevents it from working properly, so the overlay script falls back to the default data source instead.\n\nThe token apparently worked yesterday but the web source from April 1st is now stale and causing failures. The real solution would be to reload the `.env` file so the token gets recognized, but I should verify what the actual error was first—the SSL issue suggests there's a certificate validation problem with the real-time price data, not necessarily a token configuration issue.\n\nLet me trace through what the data probe shows and figure out which overlay process actually ran at 9:21 to understand the full picture.\n","thinkingSignature":"dd908c06340415112e9825f3188ad40df8f616160f4361716196ab88738cbe12"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7898m2gzgwnm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/ai_overlay/ 2>/dev/null; ls -la /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/ai_overlay/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7898m2gzgwnm_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"themis\\|ths.*level2\\|level.*2\\|同花顺\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis_upgrade_preview/s