{"type":"message","id":"17a9fe0e","parentId":"3fcdd248","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:09:30.931Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup. There are two cron jobs for the A-share fusion report:\n\n1. `A_SHARE_FUSION_REPORT_0925` - runs at 09:25 on weekdays via `a-share-fusion-report/scripts/run_fusion_report.py`\n2. Some other morning cron job that runs the overlay (that produced the 09:21 message)\n\nThe issue is:\n1. `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json` is from April 1 - it's stale (24h check)\n2. The web source fusion check is failing because the source file is too old\n\nThe \"爱马仕修复\" request is about fixing the SSL/Tushare issue. The Tushare token IS available at `~/workspace/scripts/.env` but it's not being loaded by the system when it runs the overlay cron.\n\n\nI'm realizing there's a discrepancy between the two systems. The `TUSHARE_TOKEN` exists in one location but isn't being picked up by `daily_stock_analysis_upgrade_preview`, which only has `TUSHARE_PRIORITY=2` configured. Meanwhile, the overlay system needs to refresh its stale holdings data from April 1st. I should just run the fusion report directly with Tushare configured to fix this.\n","thinkingSignature":"cfa98b011d83bf34852c4abaf1a6611dd56cbadf7800fdf92ec51762c6a75686"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b2gx9135cu1u_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 直接设置TUSHARE_TOKEN环境变量后测试thsfetcher\nTUSHARE_TOKEN=e3d8c68a414b9a84cbc49c637ec00875c7173a961eba98cff09c1afc \\\n  python3 -c \"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis_upgrade_preview')\nfrom data_provider.tushare_fetcher import TushareFetcher\nf = TushareFetcher()\nprint('API initialized:', f._api is not None)\nprint('Priority:', f.priority)\nprint('Available:', f.is_available())\nif f._api:\n    q = f.get_realtime_quote('600519')\n    print('Quote for 600519:', q)\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax