{"type":"message","id":"2e1c5c72","parentId":"693e5a8d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:09:56.091Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Tushare is working! The problem is that the `get_config()` function in the DSA project doesn't read `TUSHARE_TOKEN` from `/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/.env`. I need to find where the config is reading from and fix it.\n\nLooking at the config loading:\n```python\ntushare_token=os.getenv('TUSHARE_TOKEN'),\n```\n\nThis uses `os.getenv()` directly. The problem is that when the cron job or other automation runs, it doesn't have the `.env` file sourced.\n\nThe fix should be either:\n1. Add `source /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/.env` to the cron jobs or scripts\n\n\n2. Or configure the system environment to load the token properly\n\nBut the user specifically said they already provided the Tushare token yesterday. Looking at `/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/.env`, it does have the token there. So either the cron job isn't sourcing the `.env` file, or the config is looking elsewhere for the token. Let me check if there's a way to ensure the cron job sources the environment variables before running the Python script. The script needs to source the environment variables before executing, so I'll update the cron job to include that step. I should also verify that the fusion report's price enrichment function is properly using Tushare when available. The real issue is that `get_config()` reads from `os.getenv()`, which won't pick up variables from a `.env` file unless it's explicitly loaded. I need to either source the `.env` before running the script in the cron job, or configure the system environment with `TUSHARE_TOKEN`. The Python process itself won't automatically load `.env` files, so the cron job needs to set the environment variable explicitly before calling Python.\n","thinkingSignature":"81e0d0fc3f3faef6f46bdd1d238f462a93558e9d93639ac1f052ede49a127558"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nTushare 可以用！问题是 cron 环境没读到 `TUSHARE_TOKEN`。需要修复两件事：\n\n1. **overlay 日报脚本缺少 `TUSHARE_TOKEN` 环境变量**\n2. **enrich_holdings_with_prices.py 需要能调用 Tushare 实时价格**\n\n让我先检查 `enrich_holdings_with_prices.py` 和 cron overlay 脚本的环境：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_spacwi16zvn9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -60 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/enrich_holdings_with_prices.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_spacwi16zvn9_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/cron_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh 2>/dev/null | head -40"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":390,"output":564,"cacheRead":77952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78906,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776132572884,"responseId":"062cd4de18f5fbbc9ce055cc725a29e1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"53916c63","parentId":"2e1c5c72","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:09:56.144Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_spacwi16zvn9_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Enrich holdings CSV with latest closing prices from Tencent Finance API.\n\nUsage:\n    python3 scripts/enrich_holdings_with_prices.py \\\n        --input research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404.csv \\\n        --output research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404_enriched.csv\n\nFetches previous trading day's close price for each ticker via Tencent qt.gtimg.cn API,\nthen computes unrealized_pnl_pct = (current_price - cost_price) / cost_price * 100.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport csv\nimport sys\nimport urllib.request\nimport urllib.error\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\n# Mapping from exchange suffix to Tencent API prefix\n_EXCHANGE_MAP = {\n    \".SH\": \"sh\",   # Shanghai\n    \".SZ\": \"sz\",   # Shenzhen\n    \".HK\": \"hk\",   # Hong Kong\n}\n\n\ndef _parse_tencent_quote(raw: str) -> dict | None:\n    \"\"\"Parse a single Tencent qt.gtimg.cn quoted string.\n\n    Returns dict with keys: code, current_price, prev_close, date, change_pct\n    or None on parse failure.\n    \"\"\"\n    import re\n\n    # Extract v_XXX=\"...\" using regex to avoid semicolon-split issues\n    m = re.search(r'v_(\\w+)=\"([^\"]+)\"', raw)\n    if not m:\n        return None\n\n    code = m.group(1)  # e.g. \"sz300500\"\n    inner = m.group(2)\n    fields = inner.split(\"~\")\n\n    try:\n        # Fields: 0=51, 1=name, 2=code, 3=current, 4=prev_close,\n        #         5=open, 6=vol, ..., 30=date_time, 31=change, 32=change_pct, ...\n        current_price = float(fields[3]) if fields[3] else None\n        prev_close = float(fields[4]) if fields[4] else None\n        date_str = fields[30] if len(fields) > 30 else \"\"\n        change_pct = float(fields[32]) if len(fields) > 32 and fields[32] else None\n\n        # If current_price is 0 or missing, fall back to prev_close\n        if not current_price and prev_close:\n            current_price = prev_close\n\n        return {"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":20,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Enrich holdings CSV with latest closing prices from Tencent Finance API.\n\nUsage:\n    python3 scripts/enrich_holdings_with_prices.py \\\n        --input research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404.csv \\\n        --output research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404_enriched.csv\n\nFetches previous trading day's close price for each ticker via Tencent qt.gtimg.cn API,\nthen computes unrealized_pnl_pct = (current_price - cost_price) / cost_price * 100.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport csv\nimport sys\nimport urllib.request\nimport urllib.error\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\n# Mapping from exchange suffix to Tencent API prefix\n_EXCHANGE_MAP = {\n    \".SH\": \"sh\",   # Shanghai\n    \".SZ\": \"sz\",   # Shenzhen\n    \".HK\": \"hk\",   # Hong Kong\n}\n\n\ndef _parse_tencent_quote(raw: str) -> dict | None:\n    \"\"\"Parse a single Tencent qt.gtimg.cn quoted string.\n\n    Returns dict with keys: code, current_price, prev_close, date, change_pct\n    or None on parse failure.\n    \"\"\"\n    import re\n\n    # Extract v_XXX=\"...\" using regex to avoid semicolon-split issues\n    m = re.search(r'v_(\\w+)=\"([^\"]+)\"', raw)\n    if not m:\n        return None\n\n    code = m.group(1)  # e.g. \"sz300500\"\n    inner = m.group(2)\n    fields = inner.split(\"~\")\n\n    try:\n        # Fields: 0=51, 1=name, 2=code, 3=current, 4=prev_close,\n        #         5=open, 6=vol, ..., 30=date_time, 31=change, 32=change_pct, ...\n        current_price = float(fields[3]) if fields[3] else None\n        prev_close = float(fields[4]) if fields[4] else None\n        date_str = fields[30] if len(fields) > 30 else \"\"\n        change_pct = float(fields[32]) if len(fields) > 32 and fields[32] else None\n\n        # If current_price is 0 or missing, fall back to prev_close\n        if not current_price and prev_close:\n            current_price = prev_close\n\n        return {","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776132596138}}
{"type":"message","id":"c7724139","parentId":"53916c63","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:09:56.150Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_spacwi16zvn9_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\nWORKSPACE_ROOT=\"$(cd \"$ROOT/../..\" && pwd)\"\nPUSH_SCRIPT=\"$WORKSPACE_ROOT/scripts/push_investment_research_paper_execution.py\"\ncd \"$ROOT\"\n\n# 非交易日跳过\nMKT_OK=$(python3 -c \"\nimport urllib.request, datetime\ntry:\n    req = urllib.request.Request('https://qt.gtimg.cn/q=sh000001', headers={'User-Agent':'Mozilla/5.0'})\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=5) as r:\n        c = r.read().decode('gbk', errors='replace')\n    for line in c.split(';'):\n        parts = line.split('~')\n        if len(parts) > 30:\n            mkt = parts[30].strip()[:8]\n            today = datetime.datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d')\n            print('yes' if mkt == today else 'no')\n            break\n    else:\n        print('no')\nexcept:\n    print('yes')\n\" 2>/dev/null)\nif [[ \"$MKT_OK\" != \"yes\" ]]; then\n    echo \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')] 非 A 股交易日，跳过 paper_profiles_v1 cron\"\n    exit 0\nfi\n\nPYRUN=\"$ROOT/scripts/cron_python.sh\"\n\"$PYRUN\" --runtime-only\n\nexport LITELLM_LOCAL_MODEL_COST_MAP=true\n\nDATE_TAG=\"${1:-$(date +%Y%m%d)}\"\nstatus=0\nRUN_MODE=\"${PAPER_PROFILE_RUN_MODE:-eod}\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":27,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\nWORKSPACE_ROOT=\"$(cd \"$ROOT/../..\" && pwd)\"\nPUSH_SCRIPT=\"$WORKSPACE_ROOT/scripts/push_investment_research_paper_execution.py\"\ncd \"$ROOT\"\n\n# 非交易日跳过\nMKT_OK=$(python3 -c \"\nimport urllib.request, datetime\ntry:\n    req = urllib.request.Request('https://qt.gtimg.cn/q=sh000001', headers={'User-Agent':'Mozilla/5.0'})\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=5) as r:\n        c = r.read().decode('gbk', errors='replace')\n    for line in c.split(';'):\n        parts = line.split('~')\n        if len(parts) > 30:\n            mkt = parts[30].strip()[:8]\n            today = datetime.datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d')\n            print('yes' if mkt == today else 'no')\n            break\n    else:\n        print('no')\nexcept:\n    print('yes')\n\" 2>/dev/null)\nif [[ \"$MKT_OK\" != \"yes\" ]]; then\n    echo \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')] 非 A 股交易日，跳过 paper_profiles_v1 cron\"\n    exit 0\nfi\n\nPYRUN=\"$ROOT/scripts/cron_python.sh\"\n\"$PYRUN\" --runtime-only\n\nexport LITELLM_LOCAL_MODEL_COST_MAP=true\n\nDATE_TAG=\"${1:-$(date +%Y%m%d)}\"\nstatus=0\nRUN_MODE=\"${PAPER_PROFILE_RUN_MODE:-eod}\"","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776132596145}}
