{"type":"message","id":"a977f0cb","parentId":"5f8af2db","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:10:47.975Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at the sync_web_selected_holdings.py script - this might be what creates ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json from the local THS ledger files.\n","thinkingSignature":"ac33ff205a8bab11616c6ea4f387bd3c875fd26cc63c62b0d21939cf468fc6e6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_va202a67yn26_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/skills/ths-local-holdings/scripts/sync_web_selected_holdings.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":581,"output":85,"cacheRead":79872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80538,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776132640521,"responseId":"062cd5224cf6c35785a1f63a9323f715"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b57fa9c4","parentId":"a977f0cb","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:10:48.006Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_va202a67yn26_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport csv\nimport json\nimport shutil\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\nDEFAULT_SOURCE_JSON = \"ths_selected_holdings.json\"\nDEFAULT_SOURCE_CSV = \"ths_selected_holdings.csv\"\nLATEST_JSON_NAME = \"ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json\"\nLATEST_CSV_NAME = \"ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.csv\"\nLATEST_META_NAME = \"ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.meta.json\"\n\n\ndef ensure_parent(path: Path) -> None:\n    path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n\ndef load_payload(path: Path) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    payload = json.loads(path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    if not isinstance(payload, dict):\n        raise ValueError(\"source json 顶层必须是对象\")\n    holdings = payload.get(\"holdings\")\n    if not isinstance(holdings, list) or not holdings:\n        raise ValueError(\"source json 缺少非空 holdings 列表\")\n    return payload\n\n\ndef normalize_holdings_rows(payload: dict[str, Any]) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    rows: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    for item in payload.get(\"holdings\") or []:\n        if not isinstance(item, dict):\n            continue\n        row = {\n            \"symbol\": str(item.get(\"symbol\") or \"\").strip(),\n            \"asset_type\": str(item.get(\"asset_type\") or \"\").strip(),\n            \"name\": str(item.get(\"name\") or \"\").strip(),\n            \"quantity\": item.get(\"quantity\"),\n            \"cost_price\": item.get(\"cost_price\"),\n            \"source_path\": str(item.get(\"source_path\") or \"\").strip(),\n            \"ledger_ids\": item.get(\"ledger_ids\") or [],\n        }\n        if row[\"symbol\"]:\n            rows.append(row)\n    if not rows:\n        raise ValueError(\"holdings 中没有可用行\")\n    return rows\n\n\ndef write_csv(path: Path, rows: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> None:\n    ensure_parent(path)\n    with path.open(\"w\", encoding=\"utf-8-sig\", newline=\"\") as handle:\n        writer = csv.DictWriter(\n            handle,\n            fieldnames=[\"symbol\", \"asset_type\", \"name\", \"quantity\", \"cost_price\", \"source_path\", \"ledger_ids\"],\n        )\n        writer.writeheader()\n        for row in rows:\n            ledger_ids = row.get(\"ledger_ids\") or []\n            if not isinstance(ledger_ids, list):\n                ledger_ids = [str(ledger_ids)]\n            writer.writerow(\n                {\n                    \"symbol\": row.get(\"symbol\") or \"\",\n                    \"asset_type\": row.get(\"asset_type\") or \"\",\n                    \"name\": row.get(\"name\") or \"\",\n                    \"quantity\": row.get(\"quantity\") if row.get(\"quantity\") is not None else \"\",\n                    \"cost_price\": row.get(\"cost_price\") if row.get(\"cost_price\") is not None else \"\",\n                    \"source_path\": row.get(\"source_path\") or \"\",\n                    \"ledger_ids\": \"|\".join(str(x) for x in ledger_ids if str(x).strip()),\n                }\n            )\n\n\ndef build_selected_payload(source_payload: dict[str, Any], source_json_path: Path, rows: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    codes = [str(row.get(\"symbol\") or \"\") for row in rows if str(row.get(\"symbol\") or \"\").strip()]\n    return {\n        \"selected_holdings_source\": \"web\",\n        \"source\": \"web\",\n        \"upstream_source\": source_payload.get(\"source\") or \"tzzb_web_stock_position_api\",\n        \"generated_at\": datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\"),\n        \"request_url\": source_payload.get(\"request_url\") or \"\",\n        \"status_code\": source_payload.get(\"status_code\"),\n        \"summary\": source_payload.get(\"summary\") or {},\n        \"codes\": codes,\n        \"holdings\": rows,\n        \"meta\": {\n            \"synced_from\": str(source_json_path),\n            \"sync_mode\": \"replay_output_to_selected_holdings\",\n        },\n    }\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Sync replay output into fusion-report friendly selected holdings files\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--source-dir\", default=\".\", help=\"Directory containing replay outputs\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--source-json\", default=DEFAULT_SOURCE_JSON, help=\"Replay normalized JSON filename\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--source-csv\", default=DEFAULT_SOURCE_CSV, help=\"Replay normalized CSV filename\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--out-dir\", default=\".\", help=\"Target directory for selected holdings files\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--prefix\", default=\"ths_web_selected_holdings\", help=\"Timestamped output filename prefix\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    source_dir = Path(args.source_dir).expanduser().resolve()\n    out_dir = Path(args.out_dir).expanduser().resolve()\n    source_json_path = (source_dir / args.source_json).resolve()\n    source_csv_path = (source_dir / args.source_csv).resolve()\n\n    if not source_json_path.exists():\n        raise SystemExit(f\"source json 不存在: {source_json_path}\")\n\n    payload = load_payload(source_json_path)\n    rows = normalize_holdings_rows(payload)\n    selected_payload = build_selected_payload(payload, source_json_path, rows)\n\n    ts = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d_%H%M%S\")\n    stamped_json = out_dir / f\"{args.prefix}_{ts}.json\"\n    stamped_csv = out_dir / f\"{args.prefix}_{ts}.csv\"\n    latest_json = out_dir / LATEST_JSON_NAME\n    latest_csv = out_dir / LATEST_CSV_NAME\n    latest_meta = out_dir / LATEST_META_NAME\n\n    ensure_parent(stamped_json)\n    stamped_json.write_text(json.dumps(selected_payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    write_csv(stamped_csv, rows)\n    shutil.copyfile(stamped_json, latest_json)\n    shutil.copyfile(stamped_csv, latest_csv)\n\n    meta = {\n        \"source\": \"web\",\n        \"source_json\": str(source_json_path),\n        \"source_csv_exists\": source_csv_path.exists(),\n        \"output_json\": str(stamped_json),\n        \"output_csv\": str(stamped_csv),\n        \"latest_json\": str(latest_json),\n        \"latest_csv\": str(latest_csv),\n        \"holding_count\": len(rows),\n        \"a_share_symbols\": [row[\"symbol\"] for row in rows if str(row.get(\"symbol\") or \"\").endswith((\".SH\", \".SZ\", \".BJ\"))],\n    }\n    latest_meta.write_text(json.dumps(meta, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    print(json.dumps(meta, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776132647994}}
{"type":"message","id":"8fb3edfd","parentId":"b57fa9c4","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:11:15.122Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. Let me now look at how to actually run the overlay with Tushare. The user says they already connected THS Level2 today. The key issues are:\n\n1. The ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json is stale (from April 1)\n2. TUSHARE_TOKEN is not set in the environment variables used by the scripts\n3. The overlay script relies on stale data\n\nLet me check the cron job that runs the overlay. Looking at the crontab I saw earlier, there's no explicit overlay cron. But looking at the system messages, the overlay task completed at 09:21:44 but with SSL certificate issues and the runner JSON shows FAILED_CLOSED.\n \nSo the overlay ran this morning at 09:21:44, and the system message indicates the selected holdings from April 1 are what's being used to generate the overlay output. The task completed but hit an SSL certificate problem with real-time prices, yet the analysis still ran through to completion.\n\nHowever, there's a stale data issue flagged—the source file from April 1 is beyond the 24-hour threshold, so the system rejected it with FAILED_CLOSED and won't use it. The overlay itself is generated by ai_overlay, but the web_source_fusion_daily_latest.json that's supposed to provide real-time prices isn't being consumed properly due to this staleness check.\n\nLooking at the logs more carefully, the overlay actually did complete successfully with its analysis—it's just that one specific component (web_source_fusion_daily_latest) is in a failed state. The user's complaint about tushare seems to be pointing at a different problem: their token was supposedly provided yesterday, but the TUSHARE_TOKEN environment variable isn't actually set on the system, and the config isn't picking it up even though it exists in the scripts/.env file.\n\nNow I need to trace through where the overlay is actually sourcing its data and how it's trying to use Tushare, since the real-time price fetching appears to be broken at multiple levels. The overlay script itself is a Python module, so I need to trace back to see what shell script invokes it and where the environment variables are being set. Based on the cron timestamps, the overlay likely runs between 8:00 and 8:30 AM, so the Python scripts are probably being called with environment initialization from a parent shell script rather than directly from cron.\n","thinkingSignature":"90f6378776e044453b4b2f01289a2d0fce43c02da2e071c386bdc55f5573dd96"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kyhy0f0kydtk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"import.*enrich\\|enrich_holdings\\|selected_real_positions\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/ --include=\"*.py\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".pyc\\|test\\|__pycache__\" | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kyhy0f0kydtk_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/ | grep -i \"cron\\|daily\\|overlay\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1531,"output":642,"cacheRead":80448,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82621,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776132648008,"responseId":"062cd529953cc61eaf6012b3674bb9e4"}}
