{"type":"message","id":"5e66ae93","parentId":"4b92f75b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:12:14.020Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the issue! The `web_source_fusion_daily_latest.json` with `FAILED_CLOSED` is generated by the `run_fusion_report.py` script when the `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json` file is stale (older than 24 hours).\n\nThe problem is:\n1. The web source (tzzb API) is stale because it hasn't been updated since April 1\n2. The local holdings (selected_real_positions) are updated daily from local THS app files\n3. But the fusion report skill keeps trying to use `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json` as the primary source\n\n\n4. The overlay report runs through a cron job at 09:25 on weekdays, and when the health probe detected the degraded data source, it flagged the stale ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json as the root cause.\n\nThe real issue is that Tushare isn't configured in the system environment despite having the token available, so the overlay report falls back to using outdated data instead of pulling fresh information from the API.\n\nThe SSL error in the monitoring message suggests the real-time prices couldn't be fetched, but the analysis still completed—so I need to verify whether the overlay script is actually using Tushare correctly when it's configured, and then address the TUSHARE_TOKEN environment variable issue by setting it in the right profile so the system can access it. Looking at the cron job that runs at 9:25 AM on weekdays, I need to identify which script is generating that FAILED_CLOSED report and fix it. The \"爱马仕\" in the message likely refers to a component name or nickname within their system rather than the Hermès brand.\n\nThe real issue is that the overlay is trying to use web-selected holdings from April 1st instead of the local real positions from April 14th, so I should either re-sync the web holdings from the current local file or point the overlay system to use the fresh local holdings file instead. The FAILED_CLOSED status in the runner JSON seems to be generated by the a-share-fusion-report skill itself when it detects that the ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json file is stale, rather than coming from an external runner process. Looking at the content, it appears to be a monitoring output file that was written by the skill as part of its execution. to the `run_fusion_report.py` script somehow. Let me look at how the runner JSON path is determined.\n\nActually, re-reading: the system message says the overlay \"定时任务已完成\" with SSL issue. But then there's also FAILED_CLOSED in a runner JSON path. These might be two different things.\n\nThe runner JSON might be part of a different automation system that runs the fusion report and creates that status file. I should search for any automation that writes to that specific path.\n\nBut more importantly, the user's core issue is clear: they're saying Tushare token was already provided yesterday and the system should be using it. They want me to fix the SSL issue so real-time prices can be fetched.\n\nLet me check where TUSHARE_TOKEN should be configured in the shell profile.\n","thinkingSignature":"058584c6ae6fd24cb463e8f4a4d9de00cae873a86e8cd5e766879481960b6051"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n问题很清楚了。让我先确认根本原因：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8t8u8gyhmlrh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.zshrc 2>/dev/null | grep -i tushare; echo \"---\"; cat ~/.bashrc 2>/dev/null | grep -i tushare; echo \"---\"; cat /Users/ling/.profile 2>/dev/null | grep -i tushare"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8t8u8gyhmlrh_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/auto_premarket_precheck_20260414.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps({k:v for k,v in d.items() if k in ['status','overlay_report_path','overlay_