{"type":"message","id":"c792d01f","parentId":"511aac35","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:12:45.783Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `.zshrc` has a different TUSHARE_TOKEN (`fa7fe5039b58853bd0df3fc31f1770fc4a8cfaa79c6bff0473829bbc`) while the `~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/.env` has `e3d8c68a414b9a84cbc49c637ec00875c7173a961eba98cff09c1afc`. And the `personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/tushare_to_qlib_update.py` has its own hardcoded token `e3d8c68a414b9a84cbc49c637ec00875c7173a961eba98cff09c1afc`.\n\n\nThe scheduled jobs run under system crontab without shell profile loading, so they only get the Token from the hardcoded values in the scripts themselves. The primary issue is that the 09:25 A-share fusion report and overlay script aren't running because `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json` is stale and needs to be refreshed from the web source.\n\nThe real blocker is that `web_source_fusion_daily_latest.json` checks for staleness and fails when the source file is too old. I need to either update that source file from the web or bypass the staleness check so the fusion report can proceed. The THS web holdings probe has a replay command available, though I haven't confirmed whether the request JSON is saved locally. Rather than debugging that path further, I should focus on the core fix: the real problem is that real-time prices aren't being retrieved due to SSL certificate issues, not that the holdings data is unavailable. I need to fix the price fetching.\n\nKey insight: the system has Tushare token `fa7fe5039b58853bd0df3fc31f1770fc4a8cfaa79c6bff0473829bbc` in `.zshrc` (shell init), but the cron jobs don't load shell profiles and the `src.config` doesn't pick it up from environment. The `enrich_holdings_with_prices.py` script uses Tencent API (not Tushare) directly without needing a token. The solution is to make `enrich_holdings_with_prices.py` use the unified DataFetcherManager (which has THS/TDX at highest priority) instead of the Tencent API directly. Looking at `stock_level_realtime_gate_v2.py`, it already has `_get_unified_fetcher()` that uses `ThsMarketFetcher` at highest priority. I need to check if `enrich_holdings_with_prices.py` can use this same fetcher approach, or if there's a simpler way to wire Tushare into the config loading. The cleanest path forward is to first check if `sync_web_selected_holdings.py` can refresh the holdings data, then address the SSL issue in `enrich_holdings_with_prices.py`.\n","thinkingSignature":"78b0e51e2fa634ef288d612998c3735edae70fea768ffc6e62e4ae83ff177c72"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n现在问题定位清楚了：\n\n1. **`ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json` 数据过期**（4月1日 vs 今天4月14日），导致 `web_source_fusion_daily_latest.json` 报 `stale_web_source_latest` 而失败\n2. **`enrich_holdings_with_prices.py` 使用腾讯 API**（`qt.gtimg.cn`），没有使用已经配置好的同花顺/Tushare 实时行情\n\n修复方案：用 `ThsMarketFetcher`（同花顺 Level2）替换腾讯 API 获取持仓价格。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hdvop0cwotm4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -200 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/enrich_holdings_with_prices.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":317,"output":798,"cacheRead":84416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85531,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776132734121,"responseId":"062cd57f26ab5135bacece7079e75d20"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6132c8a4","parentId":"c792d01f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:12:45.826Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hdvop0cwotm4_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Enrich holdings CSV with latest closing prices from Tencent Finance API.\n\nUsage:\n    python3 scripts/enrich_holdings_with_prices.py \\\n        --input research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404.csv \\\n        --output research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404_enriched.csv\n\nFetches previous trading day's close price for each ticker via Tencent qt.gtimg.cn API,\nthen computes unrealized_pnl_pct = (current_price - cost_price) / cost_price * 100.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport csv\nimport sys\nimport urllib.request\nimport urllib.error\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\n# Mapping from exchange suffix to Tencent API prefix\n_EXCHANGE_MAP = {\n    \".SH\": \"sh\",   # Shanghai\n    \".SZ\": \"sz\",   # Shenzhen\n    \".HK\": \"hk\",   # Hong Kong\n}\n\n\ndef _parse_tencent_quote(raw: str) -> dict | None:\n    \"\"\"Parse a single Tencent qt.gtimg.cn quoted string.\n\n    Returns dict with keys: code, current_price, prev_close, date, change_pct\n    or None on parse failure.\n    \"\"\"\n    import re\n\n    # Extract v_XXX=\"...\" using regex to avoid semicolon-split issues\n    m = re.search(r'v_(\\w+)=\"([^\"]+)\"', raw)\n    if not m:\n        return None\n\n    code = m.group(1)  # e.g. \"sz300500\"\n    inner = m.group(2)\n    fields = inner.split(\"~\")\n\n    try:\n        # Fields: 0=51, 1=name, 2=code, 3=current, 4=prev_close,\n        #         5=open, 6=vol, ..., 30=date_time, 31=change, 32=change_pct, ...\n        current_price = float(fields[3]) if fields[3] else None\n        prev_close = float(fields[4]) if fields[4] else None\n        date_str = fields[30] if len(fields) > 30 else \"\"\n        change_pct = float(fields[32]) if len(fields) > 32 and fields[32] else None\n\n        # If current_price is 0 or missing, fall back to prev_close\n        if not current_price and prev_close:\n            current_price = prev_close\n\n        return {\n            \"code\": code,\n            \"current_price\": current_price,\n            \"prev_close\": prev_close,\n            \"date\": date_str,\n            \"change_pct\": change_pct,\n        }\n    except (ValueError, IndexError):\n        return None\n\n\ndef fetch_prices(tickers: list[str]) -> dict[str, dict]:\n    \"\"\"Fetch latest close prices for all tickers via Tencent qt.gtimg.cn.\n\n    Returns dict mapping exchange-prefixed ticker (e.g. 'sz300500') -> price dict.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Build query string\n    qt_tickers = []\n    for t in tickers:\n        for suffix, prefix in _EXCHANGE_MAP.items():\n            if t.endswith(suffix):\n                qt_tickers.append(prefix + t.replace(suffix, \"\"))\n                break\n\n    query = \",\".join(qt_tickers)\n    url = f\"https://qt.gtimg.cn/q={query}\"\n\n    req = urllib.request.Request(url, headers={\"User-Agent\": \"Mozilla/5.0\"})\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=10) as resp:\n            raw = resp.read().decode(\"gbk\", errors=\"replace\")\n    except (urllib.error.URLError, OSError) as exc:\n        print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Failed to fetch prices: {exc}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return {}\n\n    # Extract each v_XXX=\"...\" block with regex (semicolons appear inside quoted values)\n    import re\n    result = {}\n    for m in re.finditer(r'v_(\\w+)=\"([^\"]+)\"', raw):\n        parsed = _parse_tencent_quote(m.group(0))\n        if parsed:\n            result[parsed[\"code\"]] = parsed\n    return result\n\n\ndef main() -> int:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Enrich holdings CSV with latest closing prices\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--input\", \"-i\", required=True, help=\"Input holdings CSV\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--output\", \"-o\", required=True, help=\"Output enriched CSV\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\n    if not input_path.exists():\n        print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Input file not found: {input_path}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return 1\n\n    # Read holdings\n    holdings: list[dict] = []\n    with input_path.open(newline=\"\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        reader = csv.DictReader(f)\n        holdings = list(reader)\n\n    tickers = [h[\"symbol\"] for h in holdings]\n    print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Fetching prices for {len(tickers)} tickers...\")\n\n    price_map = fetch_prices(tickers)\n    print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Got prices for {len(price_map)} tickers\")\n\n    # Enrich holdings\n    enriched: list[dict] = []\n    for h in holdings:\n        h = dict(h)\n        symbol = h[\"symbol\"]\n        cost_str = h.get(\"cost_price\", \"0\")\n        try:\n            cost = float(cost_str)\n        except (ValueError, TypeError):\n            cost = 0.0\n\n        # Find price\n        current_price = None\n        prev_close = None\n        change_pct = None\n\n        for suffix, prefix in _EXCHANGE_MAP.items():\n            if symbol.endswith(suffix):\n                qt_key = prefix + symbol.replace(suffix, \"\")\n                if qt_key in price_map:\n                    p = price_map[qt_key]\n                    current_price = p[\"current_price\"]\n                    prev_close = p[\"prev_close\"]\n                    change_pct = p[\"change_pct\"]\n                break\n\n        h[\"current_price\"] = str(current_price) if current_price is not None else \"\"\n        h[\"prev_close\"] = str(prev_close) if prev_close is not None else \"\"\n        h[\"change_pct_today\"] = str(change_pct) if change_pct is not None else \"\"\n\n        if current_price and cost and cost > 0:\n            pnl_pct = (current_price - cost) / cost * 100\n            h[\"unrealized_pnl_pct\"] = f\"{pnl_pct:.2f}\"\n            mkt_val = current_price * float(h.get(\"quantity\", 0))\n            h[\"market_value\"] = f\"{mkt_val:.2f}\"\n        else:\n            h[\"unrealized_pnl_pct\"] = \"\"\n            h[\"market_value\"] = \"\"\n\n        enriched.append(h)\n\n    # Write enriched CSV\n    output_path = Path(args.output)\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    if enriched:\n        fieldnames = list(enriched[0].keys())\n        with open(output_path, \"w\", newline=\"\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n            writer = csv.DictWriter(f, fieldnames=fieldnames)\n            writer.writeheader()\n            writer.writerows(enriched)\n\n    print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Written {len(enriched)} enriched rows to {output_path}\")\n\n    # Print summary\n    print(\"\\n=== Price Summary ===\")\n    for h in enriched:\n        pnl = h.get(\"unrealized_pnl_pct\", \"N/A\")\n        cur = h.get(\"current_price\", \"N/A\")\n        chg = h.get(\"change_pct_today\", \"\")\n        chg_str = f\"{float(chg):+.2f}%\" if chg else \"\"\n        print(f\"  {h['symbol']:15s} {h.get('name',''):10s}  cur={cur:>8s}  cost={h.get('cost_price',''):>8s}  pnl={pnl:>8s}%  today={chg_str}\")\n    return 0\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":18,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Enrich holdings CSV with latest closing prices from Tencent Finance API.\n\nUsage:\n    python3 scripts/enrich_holdings_with_prices.py \\\n        --input research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404.csv \\\n        --output research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260404_enriched.csv\n\nFetches previous trading day's close price for each ticker via Tencent qt.gtimg.cn API,\nthen computes unrealized_pnl_pct = (current_price - cost_price) / cost_price * 100.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport csv\nimport sys\nimport urllib.request\nimport urllib.error\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\n# Mapping from exchange suffix to Tencent API prefix\n_EXCHANGE_MAP = {\n    \".SH\": \"sh\",   # Shanghai\n    \".SZ\": \"sz\",   # Shenzhen\n    \".HK\": \"hk\",   # Hong Kong\n}\n\n\ndef _parse_tencent_quote(raw: str) -> dict | None:\n    \"\"\"Parse a single Tencent qt.gtimg.cn quoted string.\n\n    Returns dict with keys: code, current_price, prev_close, date, change_pct\n    or None on parse failure.\n    \"\"\"\n    import re\n\n    # Extract v_XXX=\"...\" using regex to avoid semicolon-split issues\n    m = re.search(r'v_(\\w+)=\"([^\"]+)\"', raw)\n    if not m:\n        return None\n\n    code = m.group(1)  # e.g. \"sz300500\"\n    inner = m.group(2)\n    fields = inner.split(\"~\")\n\n    try:\n        # Fields: 0=51, 1=name, 2=code, 3=current, 4=prev_close,\n        #         5=open, 6=vol, ..., 30=date_time, 31=change, 32=change_pct, ...\n        current_price = float(fields[3]) if fields[3] else None\n        prev_close = float(fields[4]) if fields[4] else None\n        date_str = fields[30] if len(fields) > 30 else \"\"\n        change_pct = float(fields[32]) if len(fields) > 32 and fields[32] else None\n\n        # If current_price is 0 or missing, fall back to prev_close\n        if not current_price and prev_close:\n            current_price = prev_close\n\n        return {\n            \"code\": code,\n            \"current_price\": current_price,\n            \"prev_close\": prev_close,\n            \"date\": date_str,\n            \"change_pct\": change_pct,\n        }\n    except (ValueError, IndexError):\n        return None\n\n\ndef fetch_prices(tickers: list[str]) -> dict[str, dict]:\n    \"\"\"Fetch latest close prices for all tickers via Tencent qt.gtimg.cn.\n\n    Returns dict mapping exchange-prefixed ticker (e.g. 'sz300500') -> price dict.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Build query string\n    qt_tickers = []\n    for t in tickers:\n        for suffix, prefix in _EXCHANGE_MAP.items():\n            if t.endswith(suffix):\n                qt_tickers.append(prefix + t.replace(suffix, \"\"))\n                break\n\n    query = \",\".join(qt_tickers)\n    url = f\"https://qt.gtimg.cn/q={query}\"\n\n    req = urllib.request.Request(url, headers={\"User-Agent\": \"Mozilla/5.0\"})\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=10) as resp:\n            raw = resp.read().decode(\"gbk\", errors=\"replace\")\n    except (urllib.error.URLError, OSError) as exc:\n        print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Failed to fetch prices: {exc}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return {}\n\n    # Extract each v_XXX=\"...\" block with regex (semicolons appear inside quoted values)\n    import re\n    result = {}\n    for m in re.finditer(r'v_(\\w+)=\"([^\"]+)\"', raw):\n        parsed = _parse_tencent_quote(m.group(0))\n        if parsed:\n            result[parsed[\"code\"]] = parsed\n    return result\n\n\ndef main() -> int:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Enrich holdings CSV with latest closing prices\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--input\", \"-i\", required=True, help=\"Input holdings CSV\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--output\", \"-o\", required=True, help=\"Output enriched CSV\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\n    if not input_path.exists():\n        print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Input file not found: {input_path}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return 1\n\n    # Read holdings\n    holdings: list[dict] = []\n    with input_path.open(newline=\"\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        reader = csv.DictReader(f)\n        holdings = list(reader)\n\n    tickers = [h[\"symbol\"] for h in holdings]\n    print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Fetching prices for {len(tickers)} tickers...\")\n\n    price_map = fetch_prices(tickers)\n    print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Got prices for {len(price_map)} tickers\")\n\n    # Enrich holdings\n    enriched: list[dict] = []\n    for h in holdings:\n        h = dict(h)\n        symbol = h[\"symbol\"]\n        cost_str = h.get(\"cost_price\", \"0\")\n        try:\n            cost = float(cost_str)\n        except (ValueError, TypeError):\n            cost = 0.0\n\n        # Find price\n        current_price = None\n        prev_close = None\n        change_pct = None\n\n        for suffix, prefix in _EXCHANGE_MAP.items():\n            if symbol.endswith(suffix):\n                qt_key = prefix + symbol.replace(suffix, \"\")\n                if qt_key in price_map:\n                    p = price_map[qt_key]\n                    current_price = p[\"current_price\"]\n                    prev_close = p[\"prev_close\"]\n                    change_pct = p[\"change_pct\"]\n                break\n\n        h[\"current_price\"] = str(current_price) if current_price is not None else \"\"\n        h[\"prev_close\"] = str(prev_close) if prev_close is not None else \"\"\n        h[\"change_pct_today\"] = str(change_pct) if change_pct is not None else \"\"\n\n        if current_price and cost and cost > 0:\n            pnl_pct = (current_price - cost) / cost * 100\n            h[\"unrealized_pnl_pct\"] = f\"{pnl_pct:.2f}\"\n            mkt_val = current_price * float(h.get(\"quantity\", 0))\n            h[\"market_value\"] = f\"{mkt_val:.2f}\"\n        else:\n            h[\"unrealized_pnl_pct\"] = \"\"\n            h[\"market_value\"] = \"\"\n\n        enriched.append(h)\n\n    # Write enriched CSV\n    output_path = Path(args.output)\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    if enriched:\n        fieldnames = list(enriched[0].keys())\n        with open(output_path, \"w\", newline=\"\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n            writer = csv.DictWriter(f, fieldnames=fieldnames)\n            writer.writeheader()\n            writer.writerows(enriched)\n\n    print(f\"[enrich_holdings] Written {len(enriched)} enriched rows to {output_path}\")\n\n    # Print summary\n    print(\"\\n=== Price Summary ===\")\n    for h in enriched:\n        pnl = h.get(\"unrealized_pnl_pct\", \"N/A\")\n        cur = h.get(\"current_price\", \"N/A\")\n        chg = h.get(\"change_pct_today\", \"\")\n        chg_str = f\"{float(chg):+.2f}%\" if chg else \"\"\n        print(f\"  {h['symbol']:15s} {h.get('name',''):10s}  cur={cur:>8s}  cost={h.get('cost_price',''):>8s}  pnl={pnl:>8s}%  today={chg_str}\")\n    return 0\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776132765819}}
{"type":"message","id":"c6841f2e","parentId":"6132c8a4","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:13:24.407Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the issue clearly. The `enrich_holdings_with_prices.py` script uses Tencent API (`qt.gtimg.cn`) which failed due to SSL certificate issues (the morning report mentioned this). And `web_source_fusion_daily_latest.json` shows `status: \"FAILED_CLOSED\"` because the source file `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json` is stale (generated on 2026-04-01, > 24 hours old).\n\nThe root problem:\n1. **No fresh web holdings** - The web scraping of tonghuashun tzzb hasn't run since April 1\n2. **No Tushare token configured** in the environment where these scripts run (TUSHARE_TOKEN is set in .zshrc but not picked up by cron/systemd)\n\n\n3. **enrich_holdings_with_prices.py** lacks a fallback to Tushare when Tencent fails\n\nThe real issue is that the overlay system is failing because `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.json` is stale, not because of the SSL errors. The fusion report checks for fresh holdings and fails if they're more than 24 hours old, so I need to either refresh those holdings files or adjust the staleness threshold.\n\nActually, I have another option. The system has local THS app ledger files and the `ths_local_holdings` skill can extract holdings from them—there's even a `ths_selected_holdings.json` from April 9 in the coding-agent workspace. The real problem is that the overlay report's JSON check is overly strict. I should make it more robust by using local THS holdings as a fallback when web sources are stale, and add Tushare as a backup price source when the primary Tencent API fails.\n","thinkingSignature":"bde8c200ed760aa402bfd4a497e0e361ced489e780672b46f89d5e2ddad9bd1f"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找到问题了。让我先看持仓文件能不能用，同时确认一下昨天给的 token：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a8hr1fsveisq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查本地THS账本文件读取能力\npython3 -c \"\nfrom pathlib import Path\nledger_path = Path.home() / 'Library/Containers/cn.com.10jqka.macstockPro/Data/Documents/XcsFold'\nfiles = list(ledger_path.glob('XcsLscjDataFile_*'))\nprint('Found ledger files:', len(files))\nfor f in files:\n    print(' -', f.name, f'{f.stat().st_size/1024:.1f}KB')\n\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a8hr1fsveisq_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 快速读取本地THS账本数据\npython3 -c \"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '~/.openclaw/skills/ths-local-holdings/scripts'.replace('~', '/Users/ling'))\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# 读取4月14日的selected_real_positions（就是今天本地的持仓）\nsp = Path('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/selected_real_positions_20260414.csv')\nprint('Today holdings CSV exists:', sp.exists())\nprint('Last modified:', sp.stat().st_mtime if sp.exists() else 'N/A')\n\n# 读取ths_selected_holdings.json（coding-agent目录的本地账本）\nth = Path('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent/ths_selected_holdings.json')\nprint('THS local holdings JSON exists:', th.exists())\nif th.exists():\n    import json\n    d = json.load(open(th))\n    codes = d.get('summary',{}).get('symbols',[])\n    print('THS symbols count:', len(codes))\n    print('First 5:', codes[:5])\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1886,"output":770,"cacheRead":84672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87328,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776132765827,"responseId":"062cd59fe921676fbab49e4da0b37725"}}
