{"type":"message","id":"9244649f","parentId":"5b7c54cf","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:14:36.097Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n\n1. `cron_python.sh` doesn't set TUSHARE_TOKEN at all\n2. `enrich_holdings_with_prices.py` uses Tencent API (qt.gtimg.cn) - not Tushare\n3. The Tushare token is in `~/.zshrc` but cron jobs don't source that\n4. The A-share overlay system is entirely independent of the DSA upgrade preview system\n\nThe SSL error mentioned in the overlay report was about the Tencent API (`qt.gtimg.cn`), not Tushare.\n\nThe fix is:\n1. Add `export TUSHARE_TOKEN=e3d8c68a414b9a84cbc49c637ec00875c7173a961eba98cff09c1afc` to `cron_python.sh` (or the overlay scripts)\n\n\n2. Then I need to modify `enrich_holdings_with_prices.py` to use the unified DataFetcherManager from DSA instead of calling Tencent directly\n\nThe user mentioned Level 2 quotes from THS, but I should verify if that's actually available through their API or if I need to explore a different approach for accessing market data. I need to figure out whether the user's comment about \"Level 2 quotes\" is referring to the THS local app data or something else, since the system prompt mentioned the data source probe completed successfully at 09:21, but then reported a stale source error at 09:26 for the overlay report generation.\n\nLooking at the timestamps more carefully - there's a 5-minute gap between when the overlay report succeeded and when the stale data error occurred, which suggests these are separate processes. The overlay report was actually working, so the stale source error might be happening in a different pipeline or cron job that I'm not immediately seeing in the logs.\n\nThe real problem seems to be that when I queried the config, Tushare wasn't configured despite the user thinking they had provided it yesterday. They also mentioned enabling Level 2 quotes, but that wouldn't directly solve the Tushare token issue. I need to add the Tushare token to the cron job environment so it's available when the overlay runs, and then figure out whether `enrich_holdings_with_prices.py` can use it or if I need another approach to handle the SSL certificate problem they're experiencing. The core issue is that my script relies on Tencent API which has SSL problems, so I need to route through Tushare instead using the local app credentials. Since THS local holdings are already parsed and working, I can leverage the `ths_local_holdings.py` script to read directly from the app.\n\nMy plan: add Tushare token to the cron environment, test the `DataFetcherManager` with THS as the primary source for real-time quotes, then update the overlay scripts to use this approach. I should also fix the environment sourcing in `cron_python.sh` and check what the 09:21 overlay report actually generated.\n","thinkingSignature":"f579f29e6546182933f8deaae5850c81a0f27af5f3ce360512b82b10e04f4d5d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p908sm69f52r_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 确认Tushare实时行情配合THS优先级可以正常工作\nTUSHARE_TOKEN=e3d8c68a414b9a84cbc49c637ec00875c7173a961eba98cff09c1afc \\\n  python3 -c \"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis_upgrade_preview')\nfrom data_provider.base import DataFetcherManager\nfrom data_provider.ths_market_fetcher import ThsMarketFetcher\nfrom data_provider.tushare_fetcher import TushareFetcher\nfrom data_provider.akshare_fetcher import AkshareFetcher\n\n# THS为主源（已开通level2），Tushare为备用\nfetchers = [ThsMarketFetcher(), TushareFetcher(), AkshareFetcher()]\nmgr = DataFetcherManager(fetchers=fetchers)\n\n# 测试持仓中的股票\ntest_codes = ['300500.SZ', '002963.SZ', '002820.SZ', '600031.SH', '06969.HK']\nfor code in test_codes:\n    q = mgr.get_realtime_quote(code)\n    if q and q.price and q.price > 0:\n        print(f'{code}: {q.name} price={q.price} change={q.change_pct}% source={q.source}')\n    else:\n        print(f'{code}: unavailable')\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":685,"output":928,"cacheRead":87104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88717,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776132824249,"responseId":"062cd5d9d7301f00a6e0df6ee3f0cb34"}}
