{"type":"message","id":"106945d5","parentId":"937f70e7","timestamp":"2026-04-14T08:14:50.737Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_br46yh5uisqv_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\nWORKSPACE_ROOT=\"$(cd \"$ROOT/../..\" && pwd)\"\nPUSH_SCRIPT=\"$WORKSPACE_ROOT/scripts/push_investment_research_paper_execution.py\"\ncd \"$ROOT\"\n\n# 非交易日跳过（qt.gtimg.cn 公开数据用 http 避免 Python 3.14 SSL 验证问题）\nMKT_OK=$(python3 -c \"\nimport urllib.request, datetime\ntry:\n    req = urllib.request.Request('http://qt.gtimg.cn/q=sh000001', headers={'User-Agent':'Mozilla/5.0'})\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=5) as r:\n        c = r.read().decode('gbk', errors='replace')\n    for line in c.split(';'):\n        parts = line.split('~')\n        if len(parts) > 30:\n            mkt = parts[30].strip()[:8]\n            today = datetime.datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d')\n            print('yes' if mkt == today else 'no')\n            break\n    else:\n        print('no')\nexcept:\n    print('yes')\n\" 2>/dev/null)\nif [[ \"$MKT_OK\" != \"yes\" ]]; then\n    echo \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')] 非 A 股交易日，跳过 paper_profiles_v1 cron\"\n    exit 0\nfi\n\nPYRUN=\"$ROOT/scripts/cron_python.sh\"\n\"$PYRUN\" --runtime-only\n\nexport LITELLM_LOCAL_MODEL_COST_MAP=true\n\nDATE_TAG=\"${1:-$(date +%Y%m%d)}\"\nstatus=0\nRUN_MODE=\"${PAPER_PROFILE_RUN_MODE:-eod}\"\nRUN_HEAVY_REPORTS=\"${PAPER_PROFILE_RUN_HEAVY_REPORTS:-}\"\n\nif [[ -z \"$RUN_HEAVY_REPORTS\" ]]; then\n  if [[ \"$RUN_MODE\" == \"morning_open\" ]]; then\n    RUN_HEAVY_REPORTS=\"0\"\n  else\n    RUN_HEAVY_REPORTS=\"1\"\n  fi\nfi\n\nif PAPER_PROFILE_RUN_HEAVY_REPORTS=\"$RUN_HEAVY_REPORTS\" bash scripts/run_paper_trading_profiles_auto_v1.sh \"$DATE_TAG\" \"\" \"$RUN_MODE\"; then\n  :\nelse\n  status=$?\n  echo \"[WARN] paper profile refresh failed date=${DATE_TAG} exit=${status}\" >&2\nfi\n\nif [[ $status -eq 0 && \"$RUN_HEAVY_REPORTS\" == \"1\" && -f \"$PUSH_SCRIPT\" ]]; then\n  if ! \"$PYRUN\" \"$PUSH_SCRIPT\" --date-tag \"$DATE_TAG\"; then\n    echo \"[WARN] paper execution push failed date=${DATE_TAG}\" >&2\n  fi\nfi\n\nif [[ \"$RUN_HEAVY_REPORTS\" == \"1\" ]]; then\n  \"$PYRUN\" scripts/generate_stock_lens_dashboard.py\n  \"$PYRUN\" scripts/generate_strategy_performance_panel.py\n  \"$PYRUN\" scripts/generate_control_tower_daily.py\n  if ! \"$PYRUN\" scripts/push_control_tower_alert_if_changed.py; then\n    echo \"[WARN] control tower alert push failed date=${DATE_TAG}\" >&2\n  fi\n  \"$PYRUN\" scripts/generate_cto_real_data_dashboard.py\n  \"$PYRUN\" scripts/generate_dashboard_portal.py\nfi\n\nexit \"$status\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776154490713}}
{"type":"message","id":"d1ef23e6","parentId":"106945d5","timestamp":"2026-04-14T08:15:22.111Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The MKT_OK check already uses `http://qt.gtimg.cn` (not `https://`), so SSL is not the issue for paper_profiles_cron. The SSL issue I tested earlier was with `https://`. So the MKT_OK check in paper_profiles is already using http, which avoids the SSL problem.\n\nNow let me think about the actual reason why the 08:25 cron ran but found no signals. Looking at the precheck result:\n- `pending_after_gate=0` - no signals passed the gate\n- `Sharpe偏低于0.800` - the strategy gate blocked everything\n\nThis is the strategy's Sharpe ratio (0.759) being below the threshold (0.800). The pipeline ran, signals were generated but all blocked by the gate.\n \nI'm realizing the distinction now—the cron script checks MKT_OK to skip on non-trading days, but when it does run, it's in morning_open mode by default since RUN_MODE isn't set to \"eod\". So the precheck was running in that mode rather than the end-of-day mode I initially thought.\n\nLooking at the precheck result, there were 0 raw rows and 0 pending raw, which suggests the signal generation pipeline itself had no signals to evaluate. But the cron log shows the 08:25 job executed, so something must have run. The logs indicate MKT_OK detected \"no\" at 08:25, yet the job still appears to have executed with non-zero output, so I need to trace through what's actually happening in the logs to understand where the discrepancy is.\n\nThe core issue is that the precheck failed with BUY_HALT and no signals, yet the user expects a push notification. I should fix the SSL issue in the MKT_OK check, address the missing intraday cron by adding a 13:30 recheck, and then dig into why run_live_execution_v1.py returned `raw_rows: 0` when there should be candidate generation happening. Let me first address the SSL problem since that's a quick fix, then investigate the signal gene