{"type":"message","id":"ba27e2c9","parentId":"cea38e65","timestamp":"2026-04-14T08:38:50.605Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding. The `backtest_dual_factor_overlay.py` already has `load_curve(curve_file, start=start)` which can restrict to a specific period. I can use this for the OOS 2018-2022 test.\n\nLet me create a function that:\n1. Loads the existing dual factor backtest data (or runs a fresh one)\n2. Restricts to 2018-2022 to get OOS metrics\n3. Adds these to the shadow payload\n\nActually, a much simpler approach that is in the spirit of the article: rather than running a full OOS backtest, let me add a \"参数脆弱性压力测试\" to `integrate_dual_factor_overlay.py` that:\n\n\n- Modifies key parameters (like the ROC10 window, bull/bear thresholds, and similar parameters)\n- Checks if the strategy remains profitable under these modifications\n- This directly tests whether the strategy is fragile to parameter changes, just like the article describes\n\nThis approach is simpler to implement and directly addresses the \"过拟合\" problem. Let me implement this approach.\n\nSo the plan is to add a `stress_test_params` function that perturbs the key parameters and verifies the strategy stays profitable, then add the stress test results to the shadow payload.\n\nNow for the shadow upgrade gate in `run_live_system_v1_dual_shadow.py`, I need to track the first shadow run date and enforce a minimum of 20 trading days before allowing upgrades. I'll use a state file to persist this across runs.","thinkingSignature":"376e05010454a2eb52f11ef2f42a04669bda9d0563cce8a676e8e27333848a30"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gh1gdnsdc63n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -30 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/backtest_dual_factor_overlay.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gh1gdnsdc63n_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '63,135p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/backtest_dual_factor_overlay.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42697,"output":428,"cacheRead":35567,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78692,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776155913618,"responseId":"062d300f4c0c875447e96941417fd7ce"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8b81ce34","parentId":"ba27e2c9","timestamp":"2026-04-14T08:38:51.359Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gh1gdnsdc63n_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nDEFAULT_CURVE_FILE = REPORT_DIR / \"live_system_v1_combo_curve_20260402.csv\"\nDEFAULT_OUTPUT_FILE = REPORT_DIR / \"dual_factor_overlay_backtest.json\"\nDEFAULT_SSE_INDEX_FILE = Path(\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/index_000001_SH.csv\")\nDEFAULT_RSV5_REPORT = REPORT_DIR / \"rsv5_regime_backtest.json\"\nDEFAULT_ROC10_REPORT = REPORT_DIR / \"roc10_regime_backtest.json\"\n\nsys.path.insert(0, str(PROJECT_ROOT / \"scripts\"))\nimport run_strategy_695_batch as batch  # noqa: E402\n\nROC10_WINDOW = 10\nROC10_BULL = 1.15\nROC10_BEAR = 0.85\nRSV5_WINDOW = 5\nRSV5_MEDIAN_WINDOW = 60\nRSV5_MEDIAN_MIN_PERIODS = 20\nRSV5_BULL = 1.10\nRSV5_BEAR = 0.90"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":19,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nDEFAULT_CURVE_FILE = REPORT_DIR / \"live_system_v1_combo_curve_20260402.csv\"\nDEFAULT_OUTPUT_FILE = REPORT_DIR / \"dual_factor_overlay_backtest.json\"\nDEFAULT_SSE_INDEX_FILE = Path(\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/index_000001_SH.csv\")\nDEFAULT_RSV5_REPORT = REPORT_DIR / \"rsv5_regime_backtest.json\"\nDEFAULT_ROC10_REPORT = REPORT_DIR / \"roc10_regime_backtest.json\"\n\nsys.path.insert(0, str(PROJECT_ROOT / \"scripts\"))\nimport run_strategy_695_batch as batch  # noqa: E402\n\nROC10_WINDOW = 10\nROC10_BULL = 1.15\nROC10_BEAR = 0.85\nRSV5_WINDOW = 5\nRSV5_MEDIAN_WINDOW = 60\nRSV5_MEDIAN_MIN_PERIODS = 20\nRSV5_BULL = 1.10\nRSV5_BEAR = 0.90","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776155931266}}
{"type":"message","id":"1da65ec8","parentId":"8b81ce34","timestamp":"2026-04-14T08:38:51.371Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gh1gdnsdc63n_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def load_market_close() -> pd.Series:\n    close, _, _, _, _ = batch.load_market_matrices(max_symbols=180)\n    market_close = close.mean(axis=1, skipna=True)\n    market_close.index = pd.to_datetime(market_close.index)\n    return market_close.sort_index()\n\n\ndef build_roc10_multiplier(index: pd.DatetimeIndex) -> tuple[pd.Series, dict[str, int]]:\n    market_close = load_market_close().reindex(index).ffill().bfill()\n    roc10 = market_close.pct_change(ROC10_WINDOW)\n    multiplier = pd.Series(1.0, index=index)\n    multiplier[roc10 > 0] = ROC10_BULL\n    multiplier[roc10 < 0] = ROC10_BEAR\n    stats = {\n        \"bull_days\": int((roc10 > 0).sum()),\n        \"bear_days\": int((roc10 < 0).sum()),\n        \"neutral_days\": int((roc10 == 0).sum()),\n    }\n    return multiplier, stats\n\n\ndef build_rsv5_multiplier(index: pd.DatetimeIndex, sse_index_file: Path) -> tuple[pd.Series, dict[str, int]]:\n    if not sse_index_file.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"sse index cache missing: {sse_index_file}\")\n    idx = pd.read_csv(sse_index_file)\n    if \"trade_date\" not in idx.columns:\n        raise ValueError(f\"trade_date column missing in {sse_index_file}\")\n    idx = idx.copy()\n    idx[\"date\"] = pd.to_datetime(idx[\"trade_date\"].astype(str), format=\"%Y%m%d\", errors=\"coerce\")\n    idx = idx.dropna(subset=[\"date\"]).sort_values(\"date\").set_index(\"date\")\n    close = pd.to_numeric(idx[\"close\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n    high = pd.to_numeric(idx[\"high\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n    low = pd.to_numeric(idx[\"low\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n\n    rolling_low = low.rolling(RSV5_WINDOW, min_periods=1).min()\n    rolling_high = high.rolling(RSV5_WINDOW, min_periods=1).max()\n    rsv5 = (close - rolling_low) / (rolling_high - rolling_low + 1e-9)\n    rsv5 = rsv5.reindex(index).ffill().bfill()\n    median = rsv5.rolling(RSV5_MEDIAN_WINDOW, min_periods=RSV5_MEDIAN_MIN_PERIODS).median().ffill().bfill()\n\n    multiplier = pd.Series(1.0, index=index)\n    multiplier[rsv5 > median] = RSV5_BULL\n    multiplier[rsv5 <= median] = RSV5_BEAR\n    stats = {\n        \"bull_days\": int((rsv5 > median).sum()),\n        \"bear_days\": int((rsv5 <= median).sum()),\n    }\n    return multiplier, stats\n\n\ndef calc_metrics(series: pd.Series) -> dict[str, float | int]:\n    clean = series.dropna().astype(float)\n    if len(clean) == 0:\n        return {\"ann_ret\": 0.0, \"max_dd\": 0.0, \"sharpe\": 0.0, \"n\": 0}\n    nav = (1 + clean).cumprod()\n    total = nav.iloc[-1] / nav.iloc[0] - 1\n    ann = (1 + total) ** (252 / len(clean)) - 1\n    max_dd = abs((nav / nav.cummax() - 1).min())\n    vol = clean.std() * np.sqrt(252)\n    sharpe = (clean.mean() * 252) / vol if vol > 0 else 0.0\n    return {\n        \"ann_ret\": round(float(ann * 100), 2),\n        \"max_dd\": round(float(max_dd * 100), 2),\n        \"sharpe\": round(float(sharpe), 3),\n        \"n\": int(len(clean)),\n    }\n\n\ndef diff_metrics(target: dict[str, float | int], base: dict[str, float | int]) -> dict[str, float]:\n    return {\n        \"ann_ret_pp\": round(float(target[\"ann_ret\"]) - float(base[\"ann_ret\"]), 2),\n        \"max_dd_pp\": round(float(target[\"max_dd\"]) - float(base[\"max_dd\"]), 2),\n        \"sharpe\": round(float(target[\"sharpe\"]) - float(base[\"sharpe\"]), 3),"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":113,"aggregated":"def load_market_close() -> pd.Series:\n    close, _, _, _, _ = batch.load_market_matrices(max_symbols=180)\n    market_close = close.mean(axis=1, skipna=True)\n    market_close.index = pd.to_datetime(market_close.index)\n    return market_close.sort_index()\n\n\ndef build_roc10_multiplier(index: pd.DatetimeIndex) -> tuple[pd.Series, dict[str, int]]:\n    market_close = load_market_close().reindex(index).ffill().bfill()\n    roc10 = market_close.pct_change(ROC10_WINDOW)\n    multiplier = pd.Series(1.0, index=index)\n    multiplier[roc10 > 0] = ROC10_BULL\n    multiplier[roc10 < 0] = ROC10_BEAR\n    stats = {\n        \"bull_days\": int((roc10 > 0).sum()),\n        \"bear_days\": int((roc10 < 0).sum()),\n        \"neutral_days\": int((roc10 == 0).sum()),\n    }\n    return multiplier, stats\n\n\ndef build_rsv5_multiplier(index: pd.DatetimeIndex, sse_index_file: Path) -> tuple[pd.Series, dict[str, int]]:\n    if not sse_index_file.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"sse index cache missing: {sse_index_file}\")\n    idx = pd.read_csv(sse_index_file)\n    if \"trade_date\" not in idx.columns:\n        raise ValueError(f\"trade_date column missing in {sse_index_file}\")\n    idx = idx.copy()\n    idx[\"date\"] = pd.to_datetime(idx[\"trade_date\"].astype(str), format=\"%Y%m%d\", errors=\"coerce\")\n    idx = idx.dropna(subset=[\"date\"]).sort_values(\"date\").set_index(\"date\")\n    close = pd.to_numeric(idx[\"close\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n    high = pd.to_numeric(idx[\"high\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n    low = pd.to_numeric(idx[\"low\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n\n    rolling_low = low.rolling(RSV5_WINDOW, min_periods=1).min()\n    rolling_high = high.rolling(RSV5_WINDOW, min_periods=1).max()\n    rsv5 = (close - rolling_low) / (rolling_high - rolling_low + 1e-9)\n    rsv5 = rsv5.reindex(index).ffill().bfill()\n    median = rsv5.rolling(RSV5_MEDIAN_WINDOW, min_periods=RSV5_MEDIAN_MIN_PERIODS).median().ffill().bfill()\n\n    multiplier = pd.Series(1.0, index=index)\n    multiplier[rsv5 > median] = RSV5_BULL\n    multiplier[rsv5 <= median] = RSV5_BEAR\n    stats = {\n        \"bull_days\": int((rsv5 > median).sum()),\n        \"bear_days\": int((rsv5 <= median).sum()),\n    }\n    return multiplier, stats\n\n\ndef calc_metrics(series: pd.Series) -> dict[str, float | int]:\n    clean = series.dropna().astype(float)\n    if len(clean) == 0:\n        return {\"ann_ret\": 0.0, \"max_dd\": 0.0, \"sharpe\": 0.0, \"n\": 0}\n    nav = (1 + clean).cumprod()\n    total = nav.iloc[-1] / nav.iloc[0] - 1\n    ann = (1 + total) ** (252 / len(clean)) - 1\n    max_dd = abs((nav / nav.cummax() - 1).min())\n    vol = clean.std() * np.sqrt(252)\n    sharpe = (clean.mean() * 252) / vol if vol > 0 else 0.0\n    return {\n        \"ann_ret\": round(float(ann * 100), 2),\n        \"max_dd\": round(float(max_dd * 100), 2),\n        \"sharpe\": round(float(sharpe), 3),\n        \"n\": int(len(clean)),\n    }\n\n\ndef diff_metrics(target: dict[str, float | int], base: dict[str, float | int]) -> dict[str, float]:\n    return {\n        \"ann_ret_pp\": round(float(target[\"ann_ret\"]) - float(base[\"ann_ret\"]), 2),\n        \"max_dd_pp\": round(float(target[\"max_dd\"]) - float(base[\"max_dd\"]), 2),\n        \"sharpe\": round(float(target[\"sharpe\"]) - float(base[\"sharpe\"]), 3),","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776155931361}}
