aseline_ann_ret\": 23.0,\n    \"baseline_sharpe\": 1.173\n  },\n  \"oos_cold_test\": {\n    \"period\": \"2018-01-02~2022-12-30\",\n    \"status\": \"computed\",\n    \"ann_ret\": 15.04,\n    \"sharpe\": 0.867,\n    \"max_dd\": 14.56,\n    \"pass\": true,\n    \"reason\": \"\",\n    \"n\": 1215\n  },\n  \"upgrade_gate\": {\n    \"min_shadow_days\": 20,\n    \"oos_sharpe_min\": 1.0,\n    \"stress_pass_required\": true,\n    \"oos_pass_required\": true\n  },\n  \"combined_pass\": true,\n  \"recommendation\": \"PASS — 可考虑 shadow→gray 升级\"\n}","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776156208553}}
{"type":"message","id":"de095080","parentId":"183a9047","timestamp":"2026-04-14T08:43:53.018Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! The stress test works! The results are very informative:\n\n**Stress Test (压力测试)**:\n- All 6 perturbation scenarios PASSED\n- Worst case ret drop: only 4.65pp (RSV5_bull-0.10 scenario)\n- Fragility score: 0.155 (low, meaning strategy is robust to param changes)\n- Baseline ann_ret: 23.0% vs Conservative dual factor: 23.0%\n\n**OOS Cold Test (2018-2022)**:\n- ann_ret: 15.04%\n- Sharpe: 0.867 (> 0.5 threshold, PASS)\n\n\n- Max DD: 14.56%\n- 1215 trading days\n\nBut I'm noticing the OOS Sharpe came in at 0.867, which falls short of the 1.0 threshold I'd set for the upgrade gate. The combined results show PASS overall, but the upgrade requirement is Sharpe > 1.0. The current shadow has only 5 days running, so it hasn't accumulated enough days yet to meet the 20-day minimum.\n\nLooking at the performance metrics more carefully: the stress test passed, and the OOS test also passed its 0.5 threshold. The combined pass reflects both components meeting their respective gates. However, with just 5 shadow days against a 20-day requirement, upgrade_eligible would correctly be False since we need that minimum tracking period before allowing any upgrade.\n\nOn the cold period specifically—the 2018-2022 window shows a Sharpe of 0.867, which clears the 0.5 safety threshold but doesn't reach the stricter 1.0 upgrade threshold. That's reasonable; the strategy proves itself viable in difficult conditions without needing exceptional performance. For context, the strict_oos system uses 2021-2022 as its validation window, so this approach aligns with that standard.\n\nNow I need to integrate this validation into the shadow system—updating `integrate_dual_factor_overlay.py` to call the stress test and `run_live_system_v1_dual_shadow.py` to enforce the upgrade gate. I'll also need to track cumulative shadow days ac