{"type":"message","id":"b2410676","parentId":"98bacd88","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:44:49.102Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Qlib predictions file was last updated on April 13 at 00:24 (midnight). The predictions go up to 2026-04-03 (the last trading day with predictions). \n\nSo the Qlib daily prediction update ran on April 13 at midnight but only generated predictions up to April 3. This means:\n1. April 3 (清明节前夕) was the last trading day with predictions\n2. April 13 (清明节后第一天) the cron ran but didn't generate new predictions for April 7-10 (清明节假期，A股休市) or April 11 (可能有交易)\n\n\n3. There's a timing mismatch here - the cron finished running on April 13, yet the predictions file only contains data through April 3, not through April 11 or later as I'd expect.\n\nThe cron that generates Qlib predictions runs daily at 16:30 according to the crontab, but since the file was last modified on April 13 at 00:24 (midnight), it seems like something ran outside the normal schedule. The predictions themselves only extend through April 3, which is puzzling given the cron should have been executing throughout the period.\n\nSince A-share markets were closed for the Qingming Festival from April 4-6 and the prediction file only goes through April 3, the system likely skipped generating predictions during the holiday closure and hasn't resumed since the market reopened on April 7. The file modification time of 00:24 suggests a delayed or off-schedule run that still didn't extend the predictions beyond the holiday period. I'm noticing a timing mismatch here—the cron is scheduled for 16:30 but the file was updated at 00:24, suggesting either a different schedule is running or there's been a system time change. The file still shows April 3 as the latest prediction date even though the market reopened on April 7, which means predictions haven't been generated for the new trading sessions. I need to check the crontab to understand the actual schedule, and more importantly, find the script that generates the breadth predictions to see why it's not creating new entries for April 7 onwards.","thinkingSignature":"08fe1dd1f31841546453a779fdd446029edd4aaadb85728a504a54af291f99c9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b2bfv9yi62qy_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 Qlib 每日更新 cron\ncrontab -l 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"qlib\\|ml_predict\\|daily_run\\|prediction\"\necho \"---\"\n# 检查 qlib 预测脚本\nfind /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/ -name \"*qlib*daily*\" -o -name \"*run_qlib*\" -o -name \"*ml*predict*\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".pyc\" | head -10"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b2bfv9yi62qy_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 看看清明后第一天（4月7日）预测为什么断掉\npython3 -c \"\nimport pandas as pd\ndf = pd.read_csv('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/ml_dataset_full/ml_predictions_live_latest.csv')\ndf['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['date'], errors='coerce')\nprint('预测日期范围:', df['date'].min(), '~', df['date'].max())\nprint('最新10条:')\nprint(df.dropna(subset=['date']).groupby('date').size().tail(10))\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":96735,"output":715,"cacheRead":35571,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133021,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776163466030,"responseId":"062d4d8f03b6547407c1686f78da1d1d"}}
