{"type":"message","id":"5254be10","parentId":"cdb9f47b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:45:09.404Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the problem clearly:\n\n- The predictions file `ml_predictions_live_latest.csv` has predictions only up to **2026-04-03**\n- After that, there's a gap — no predictions for 04-07, 04-08, 04-09, 04-10, 04-11, 04-14\n\nWait, April 2026:\n- March 31 (Mon) - last prediction\n- April 1 (Tue) - prediction exists (10930 entries)\n- April 2 (Wed) - prediction exists (10928 entries)\n- April 3 (Thu) - prediction exists (10927 entries)\n\n\n- April 4-6 (Fri-Mon) - Qingming Festival holiday, no predictions expected\n- April 7 (Tue) - market reopened but predictions stopped, then continuing through April 11 and into this week\n- April 14 (today) - still no predictions\n\nThe data was last updated on April 13 at 00:24, which is unusual timing for a file that only contains predictions through April 3. This suggests the cron job ran but either failed to generate new predictions for the trading days after the holiday, or the file was created/modified at that timestamp but the underlying data wasn't actually refreshed.\n\nLooking at the prediction counts, April 1-3 show a jump from ~5400 to ~10900 entries per day, which is suspicious and suggests something changed in the data pipeline around that period.\n\nThe key issue is that predictions stopped after April 3 — likely because the Qlib prediction script crashed or ran out of data for the holiday period and never resumed. I should check if there's a daily cron job scheduled around 16:30 that would normally refresh these predictions, and look for any logs or scripts that might explain why the pipeline broke.","thinkingSignature":"8d283ca994ec123a51d4f565b47d02af4a65c7b8e89cda9a9022c4fc514f5c71"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_szf0lsahi1mg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 查找负责更新 ml_predictions 的脚本\nfind /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_pr