{"type":"message","id":"e02efa23","parentId":"b543f158","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:45:32.879Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the issue. The Qlib prediction file (`ml_predictions_live_latest.csv`) is updated by some script, but there's NO specific cron for updating it. The file was last modified on April 13 at 00:24, but the predictions only go up to April 3.\n\nLooking at the crontab:\n- `cron_breadth_paper_trading.sh` runs at 08:30 - this uses the predictions\n- `generate_dashboard_portal.py` runs at 16:10 - this generates the panel\n\nThe prediction file (`ml_predictions_live_latest.csv`) seems to be updated by a different mechanism. The file was last modified at 00:24 on April 13, which is unusual (midnight). This might have been done manually or by a different scheduled task.\n \nThe cron runs at 08:30 and calls `generate_extended_predictions.py` to produce the predictions, but the file modification timestamp of 00:24 suggests it ran much earlier than that—or someone executed it manually at midnight instead. Let me check the breadth paper trading script to trace where these prediction updates actually originate.","thinkingSignature":"9c4e129e040b0bddd6b866b2be47c1176756c1cb1c92440387a884f059eb90a6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gxel3p5lzkyg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -50 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/cron_breadth_paper_trading.sh"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gxel3p5lzkyg_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查预测更新的实际逻辑\ngrep -n \"ml_prediction\\|generate_extended\\|update.*predict\\|backfill\" \\\n  /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/cron_breadth_paper_trading.sh \\\n  2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":100252,"output":380,"cacheRead":35571,"cacheWrite":0,"totalToke