{"type":"message","id":"52ef845f","parentId":"7fe02d8c","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:47:14.603Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the key information! The `qlib_data` directory (`cn_data_long_2015_2026_180`) was last updated on April 5 at 16:07 - this is **清明节当天** (April 5, 2026). The Qlib data hasn't been updated since Qingming Festival.\n\nAlso, the `ml_dataset_full` directory was last modified on April 13 at 00:24, but the `tushare_qlib_split` was last modified on April 5 at 16:05.\n\nSo the Qlib prediction pipeline is broken because:\n1. The Qlib data (cn_data_long_2015_2026_180) stops at April 5 (清明节当天) - so it only has data up to April 3 (the last trading day before 清明节)\n\n\n2. The `ml_predictions_live_latest.csv` was regenerated on April 13 at 00:24 but only extended to April 3 since Qlib data was frozen at that point\n\nI need to check the Tushare daily update logs from April 7 to see why the pipeline didn't restart after the holiday ended on April 6. The file modification times show April 13 was updated later in the day, but the core issue is that the Qlib data itself is stale from April 5.\n\nThe Qlib data directory hasn't been refreshed since April 5, which means I need to run the Tushare update and Qlib daily training pipeline to extend the prediction data through today (April 14). The `daily_basic_all_2019_2026.csv` file was updated April 13 at 17:26, so Tushare data exists, but Qlib hasn't processed it yet. I should check the download logs to confirm what happened on April 7 when the market reopened.","thinkingSignature":"9b6707cc47372f79a5fb5ba9f2ec73a7c126f9c9deb6d09d3dc85767934084c1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zk7vtt52xheh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/logs/download_tushare_daily.log 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"04-07|04-08|04-09|04-10|04-11|April 7|April 8|April 9|April 10|April 11\" | head -20\necho \"===\"\ncat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/lo