{"type":"message","id":"1b5a07a3","parentId":"30f1b00f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T11:19:55.927Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oo4l3k49pv3n_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\ncd \"$ROOT\"\n\nNO_RUNTIME_LOG=0\nif [[ \"${1:-}\" == \"--no-runtime-log\" ]]; then\n  NO_RUNTIME_LOG=1\n  shift\nfi\n\nDEFAULT_PYTHON_BIN=\"python3\"\nfor candidate in \\\n  \"/usr/local/bin/python3\" \\\n  \"/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.14/bin/python3\" \\\n  \"python3\"; do\n  if command -v \"$candidate\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n    DEFAULT_PYTHON_BIN=\"$candidate\"\n    break\n  fi\ndone\n\nPYTHON_BIN=\"${QUANT_CRON_PYTHON:-$DEFAULT_PYTHON_BIN}\"\n\n# ── SSL 证书修复（Python 3.14 自带 certifi，优先使用）──────────────\n_CERTIFI_CERT=\"$(/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.14/bin/python3 -c 'import certifi; print(certifi.where())' 2>/dev/null)\"\nif [[ -n \"$_CERTIFI_CERT\" && -f \"$_CERTIFI_CERT\" ]]; then\n    export SSL_CERT_FILE=\"$_CERTIFI_CERT\"\n    export REQUESTS_CA_BUNDLE=\"$_CERTIFI_CERT\"\nfi\nunset _CERTIFI_CERT\n\n# cron 环境 PATH 不含 fnm node 路径，需要显式补全\nFNM_BIN=\"${HOME}/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/bin\"\nif [[ \":$PATH:\" != *\":${FNM_BIN}:\"* ]]; then\n  export PATH=\"${FNM_BIN}:${PATH}\"\nfi\nif ! command -v \"$PYTHON_BIN\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n  echo \"[RUNTIME] status=ERROR reason=python_not_found python=${PYTHON_BIN}\"\n  exit 127\nfi\n\nPYTHON_REAL=\"$(command -v \"$PYTHON_BIN\")\"\nPY_VERSION=\"$(\"$PYTHON_REAL\" --version 2>&1 | tr -d '\\r')\"\nPIP_FREEZE_HASH=\"$(\"$PYTHON_REAL\" - <<'PY'\nimport hashlib\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\n\ntry:\n    proc = subprocess.run(\n        [sys.executable, \"-m\", \"pip\", \"freeze\"],\n        capture_output=True,\n        text=True,\n        timeout=20,\n        check=False,\n    )\n    text = (proc.stdout or \"\").replace(\"\\r\\n\", \"\\n\")\n    print(hashlib.sha256(text.encode(\"utf-8\")).hexdigest())\nexcept Exception:\n    print(\"unavailable\")\nPY\n)\"\n\nif [[ \"$NO_RUNTIME_LOG\" != \"1\" ]]; then\n  echo \"[RUNTIME] ts=$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') python=${PYTHON_REAL} version=\\\"${PY_VERSION}\\\" pip_freeze_sha256=${PIP_FREEZE_HASH}\"\nfi\n\nif [[ \"${1:-}\" == \"--runtime-only\" ]]; then\n  exit 0\nfi\n\nexec \"$PYTHON_REAL\" \"$@\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":8,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\ncd \"$ROOT\"\n\nNO_RUNTIME_LOG=0\nif [[ \"${1:-}\" == \"--no-runtime-log\" ]]; then\n  NO_RUNTIME_LOG=1\n  shift\nfi\n\nDEFAULT_PYTHON_BIN=\"python3\"\nfor candidate in \\\n  \"/usr/local/bin/python3\" \\\n  \"/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.14/bin/python3\" \\\n  \"python3\"; do\n  if command -v \"$candidate\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n    DEFAULT_PYTHON_BIN=\"$candidate\"\n    break\n  fi\ndone\n\nPYTHON_BIN=\"${QUANT_CRON_PYTHON:-$DEFAULT_PYTHON_BIN}\"\n\n# ── SSL 证书修复（Python 3.14 自带 certifi，优先使用）──────────────\n_CERTIFI_CERT=\"$(/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.14/bin/python3 -c 'import certifi; print(certifi.where())' 2>/dev/null)\"\nif [[ -n \"$_CERTIFI_CERT\" && -f \"$_CERTIFI_CERT\" ]]; then\n    export SSL_CERT_FILE=\"$_CERTIFI_CERT\"\n    export REQUESTS_CA_BUNDLE=\"$_CERTIFI_CERT\"\nfi\nunset _CERTIFI_CERT\n\n# cron 环境 PATH 不含 fnm node 路径，需要显式补全\nFNM_BIN=\"${HOME}/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/bin\"\nif [[ \":$PATH:\" != *\":${FNM_BIN}:\"* ]]; then\n  export PATH=\"${FNM_BIN}:${PATH}\"\nfi\nif ! command -v \"$PYTHON_BIN\" >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n  echo \"[RUNTIME] status=ERROR reason=python_not_found python=${PYTHON_BIN}\"\n  exit 127\nfi\n\nPYTHON_REAL=\"$(command -v \"$PYTHON_BIN\")\"\nPY_VERSION=\"$(\"$PYTHON_REAL\" --version 2>&1 | tr -d '\\r')\"\nPIP_FREEZE_HASH=\"$(\"$PYTHON_REAL\" - <<'PY'\nimport hashlib\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\n\ntry:\n    proc = subprocess.run(\n        [sys.executable, \"-m\", \"pip\", \"freeze\"],\n        capture_output=True,\n        text=True,\n        timeout=20,\n        check=False,\n    )\n    text = (proc.stdout or \"\").replace(\"\\r\\n\", \"\\n\")\n    print(hashlib.sha256(text.encode(\"utf-8\")).hexdigest())\nexcept Exception:\n    print(\"unavailable\")\nPY\n)\"\n\nif [[ \"$NO_RUNTIME_LOG\" != \"1\" ]]; then\n  echo \"[RUNTIME] ts=$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') python=${PYTHON_REAL} version=\\\"${PY_VERSION}\\\" pip_freeze_sha256=${PIP_FREEZE_HASH}\"\nfi\n\nif [[ \"${1:-}\" == \"--runtime-only\" ]]; then\n  exit 0\nfi\n\nexec \"$PYTHON_REAL\" \"$@\"","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776165595915}}
{"type":"message","id":"28783748","parentId":"1b5a07a3","timestamp":"2026-04-14T11:20:20.249Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `cron_python.sh` just sets up environment and runs the script. There's no memory limit set. The SIGKILL is likely from the system OOM killer.\n\nLet me check if there's a simpler approach - maybe I can run the ML prediction step by step, or use a different script that doesn't require full model retraining.\n\nActually, let me look at `train_ml_factors_all_a.py` more carefully - this is the main ML training script. But the issue is the same - it needs to retrain the model which takes lots of memory.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The Qlib system has data up to 4/10. \n\nThe prediction file is stuck at 4/3 because the ML model training keeps getting killed. I'm realizing the core issue might be that we're retraining from scratch when we could leverage an existing model - the model was already trained on data through 4/11 in the previous successful run, so maybe I can modify `generate_extended_predictions.py` to load that model and just predict on the new data instead of retraining entirely.\n\nThe script is likely failing because the Qlib GBDT task is trying to load the entire 11 years of historical data, which is memory-intensive. But actually, looking at the output more carefully - it loads the data in about 107 seconds successfully, then gets killed right when model.fit() starts. That's the real bottleneck - the model fitting itself is what's causing the OOM. model fitting (instant)\n- Gets killed\n\nThis suggests the model fitting itself uses a LOT of memory and the process is being killed. \n\nLet me try a different approach: instead of running `generate_extended_predictions.py`, let me try to:\n1. Check if there's a way to use the existing model (without retraining)\n2. Or find a lighter-weight approach to get predictions for the missing dates\n\nActually, let me look at the `train_ml_factors_all_a.py` which uses `tushare_a_all` data. The `tushare_a_all/a_stock_daily_merged.csv` hasn't been updated since 3/31, so even if we run it, it won't include the latest data.\n\nThe core issue is that the prediction pipeline is broken because the model training is too memory-intensive. I'm thinking about what's actually needed to fix this: generate predictions for the missing dates, get the Qlib data updated (which is done), and then produce the actual predictions. The most direct approach would be to look for an existing model checkpoint that I could use instead of retraining from scratch.\n\nLet me check if there's already a saved model I can load.","thinkingSignature":"12762a53223bc84c52213531c8bbb0e8d4b06a080cebee970722f005e6ccb814"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hzs46sn8simu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/models/ -name \"*.pkl\" -o -name \"*.joblib\" -o -name \"*model*\" 2>/dev/null | head -10\necho \"---\"\nls -la /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/models/ 2>/dev/null | head -10"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hzs46sn8simu_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if there's a way to generate predictions using a stored model\npython3 -c \"\nimport lightgbm as lgb\nprint('LGB native API available')\n# Check if we can load a saved model\nimport pathlib\nmodels_dir = pathlib.Path('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/models')\npkl_files = list(models_dir.glob('**/*.pkl'))[:3]\nprint('Pkl files:', pkl_files)\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":116644,"output":784,"cacheRead":35571,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":152999,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776165595929,"responseId":"062d55e11d000239