{"type":"message","id":"c298d78d","parentId":"e193ffd6","timestamp":"2026-04-14T11:20:44.292Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No saved models. The system needs to train the model but it's getting OOM killed. Let me try a different approach - let me check if there's a way to run the training with lower memory settings.\n\nActually, let me think about the simplest possible fix. The issue is:\n1. Qlib data has dates up to 4/10 ✅\n2. But ML predictions stop at 4/3 ❌3. The model training fails due to memory ❌\n\nOptions:\nA. Increase memory limit and retry training (might still fail)\nB. Find a way to generate predictions without full model retraining\n\n\nC. Simplify the model or reduce dataset size\n\nLooking at the crash pattern more carefully - the model fitting is what gets killed, which suggests a memory limit on the Python process itself rather than system-wide resource exhaustion. Let me try reducing the training dataset significantly to see if that gets past the OOM issue.","thinkingSignature":"06107248f7ff02fb264270f8341d79b2abe9ba920d779937e5bd98962deb5347"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ujcmchjcctnj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try running with reduced dataset - check what qlib data size looks like\npython3 -c \"\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nqlib_dir = Path.home() / '.qlib/qlib_data/cn_data_long_2015_2026_180'\ninstruments_dir = qlib_dir / 'instruments'\nif instruments_dir.exists():\n    all_files = list(instruments_dir.glob('*.csv'))[:3]\n    print(f'Instruments CSVs: {len(list(instruments_dir.glob(\\\"*.csv\\\")))}')\n    \n# Check the features data\nfeatures_dir = qlib_dir / 'features'\nif features_dir.exists():\n    print('Features dir structure:')\n    for d in list(features_dir.glob('*'))[:3]:\n        print(f'  {d.name}')\n\" 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ujcmchjcctnj_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check the predict step more carefully - maybe we can use a simpler approach\n# The script uses get_gbdt_task which loads ALL instruments data\n# Let's try with a smaller subset first\npython3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system')\nfrom qlib.tests.config import get_gbdt_task\nfrom qlib.utils import init_instance_by_config\nimport qlib\nqlib.init(provider_uri=str(__import__('pathlib').Path.home() / '.qlib/qlib_data/cn_data_long_2015_2026_180'), region='cn')\n\ntask = get_gbdt_task(\n    handler_kwargs={'instruments': 'universe180', 'start_time': '2015-01-05', 'end_time': '2026-04-11'},\n    dataset_kwargs={'train': ('2015-01-05', '2020-12-31'), 'valid': ('2021-01-01', '2022-12-30'), 'test': ('2023-01-03', '2026-04-11')}\n)\nprint('Model config:', task['model'])\nprint()\nprint('Dataset handler:', task['dataset']['handler']['class'])\nprint('Market:', task['dataset']['handler']['kwargs']['instruments'])\nprint('Start:', task['dataset']['handler']['kwargs']['start_time'])\nprint('End:', task['dataset']['handler']['kwargs']['end_time'])\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":117521,"output":729,"cacheRead":35571,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":153821,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776165621172,"responseId":"062d55fae7ddde726718095eca9b8573"}}
