{"type":"message","id":"1fa566e2","parentId":"de524c25","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:00:31.290Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, interesting. Tushare shows:\n- 04/14 (today, Tuesday): open, pretrade 04/13\n- 04/13 (yesterday, Monday): open, pretrade 04/10\n- 04/11 (last Friday): NOT in the result (is_open=0), which is odd since 04/11 is a Friday\n\nWait, 04/11 is a Friday. But the result only shows 04/13 and 04/14. That's because the query range is start_date=04/11 to end_date=04/14, and it only shows open days. Let me check - 04/11 is a Friday and should be open. But it shows only 04/13 and 04/14.\n \nI'm second-guessing the calendar - 04/11 is indeed a Friday and should be a trading day, so let me verify the Tushare data actually includes it. Looking at the Tushare log from April 13th, it fetched data through 04/10, which suggests 04/11 should be available but the most recent Tushare data only goes through 04/10.\n\nThe stock exchange calendar shows 04/14 as open (with 04/13 as the pre-trade date) and 04/13 as open (with 04/10 as pre-trade), but 04/11 isn't showing up in the results - that's strange since it's a Friday and should be a trading day.\n\nLooking at the full calendar, 04/07 is Monday through 04/10 is Thursday (Maundy Thursday, a holiday), then 04/11 is Good Friday (also a holiday), 04/12 is Easter Sunday, and trading resumes 04/13. So the original query results make sense now - the Chinese market was closed for the Easter period.\n\nFor the cron job running at 16:30 on 04/14, it would only pull Tushare data through 04/13 since today's data isn't available yet. Since Qlib already has 04/10 as its latest entry, the cron would need to backfill 04/11, 04/13, and 04/14 to get caught up.\n\nBut there's a timing question here—the Tushare data was last updated at 16:03 on 04/13, so if the cron runs at 16:30 on 04/14, it should theoretically have access to all three days of data. I need to verify whether Tushare actually publishes data for 04/14 by that point in the day.\n\nLet me test the wrapper script to see if everything runs without errors. The generate_extended_predictions script has EXTEND_END hardcoded to 04/11, which won't match the new Qlib data through 04/13, but I can patch that dynamically in the script.","thinkingSignature":"30ccaf4c3a1e653364a898612d024578202a48d95cdff479360538c4e714aa7d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6sunkzzle58u_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 快速测试：运行 tushare_to_qlib 更新（只用 04/11-04/13，验证脚本可跑通）\ncd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && \\\n/usr/bin/python3 scripts/tushare_to_qlib_update.py --start 2026-04-11 --end 2026-04-13 2>&1 | tail -10","timeout":300}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":68761,"output":722,"cacheRead":35571,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":105054,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776171611754,"responseId":"062d6d5cd80490dd5dc1ef156814a8bf"}}
