{"type":"message","id":"5ef6d767","parentId":"fa81542a","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:00:48.658Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, interesting. When trying to update from 04/11 to 04/13, it shows \"Qlib 最新交易日: 2026-04-10\" and the dump_bin step shows no data for 04/13. This means Qlib still shows 04/10 even though we're trying to update. And then \"无数据\" for the dates after 04/10.\n\nWait - this is odd. The dump_bin verification shows no data for 04/13. But Tushare should have data for 04/11 (Friday, Easter Friday - actually Chinese markets might have different holidays). \n\nAh, I see - 04/10 is Maundy Thursday in the UK and 04/11 is Good Friday, so the Chinese stock market was likely closed for at least one of those days. The 04/13 update already fetched data for 04/08, 04/09, and 04/10, but Tushare only returned empty results for 04/11, which suggests that date wasn't a valid trading day in their system.\n\nThe core issue is that I'm trying to update Qlib with dates it already has (04/10) and dates that don't have data (04/11-04/13), which is causing the dump_bin verification to fail. I need to verify whether Tushare actually has 04/14 data available at all.","thinkingSignature":"167e65573a49448f1e72341a4929f934270a95573f8a5590427c459188b0aea2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9l3hqllmog75_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 验证今天(04/14) Tushare数据是否已有\n/usr/bin/python3 -c \"\nimport tushare as ts\nimport os\ntoken = os.getenv('TUSHARE_TOKEN', 'e3d8c68a414b9a84cbc49c637ec00875c7173a961eba98cff09c1afc')\npro = ts.pro_api(token)\n# 尝试获取今天的数据\ntry:\n    df = pro.daily(trade_date='20260414')\n    print('04/14 rows:', len(df))\n    print(df[['trade_date','close']].head(3) if len(df) > 0 else '无数据')\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print('04/14 查询失败:', e)\n\n# 同时检查 04/11 和 04/13\nfor d in ['20260411', '20260413']:\n    try:\n        df = pro.daily(trade_date=d)\n        print(f'{d}: {len(df)} rows')\n    except Exception