{"type":"message","id":"1a314bad","parentId":"78c5e818","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:04:13.670Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Qlib calendar shows 04/14 as a trading day, but when I try to read the data for SZ000001 on 04/14, it returns empty. This means the dump_update didn't actually write 04/14 data for individual stocks.\n\nLooking at the issue:\n1. The dump_update reported \"✅ dump_update 成功\" but showed 2 files processed (daily_20260413.csv, daily_20260414.csv)\n2. However, the verification showed \"SZ000001 @ 20260414: 无数据\"\n3. And now when I query directly, SZ000001 has no data for 04/14\n   \nI think the problem is that daily_20260414.csv already existed in the tushare_raw directory from an earlier failed run, so dump_update reused it without actually fetching fresh data from Tushare for that date.\n\nLooking at the file timestamps, daily_20260413.csv and daily_20260414.csv both show April 13 modification dates, which explains why they're being skipped as \"already exists.\" But if 20260414.csv contains incomplete or empty data from that failed earlier attempt, dump_update would have processed an invalid file. I need to delete these CSVs and rerun the process to ensure we get fresh, complete data.","thinkingSignature":"6741aa8b6170a6255e85d0532155fb523aad5877d55f2f6cc4b8c6e66e397ddf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i7ll8k43q9b2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查原始 CSV 数据的完整性\nls -la /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/tushare_raw/daily_2026041*.csv 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\n/usr/bin/python3 -c \"\nimport pandas as pd\nfor f in ['daily_20260413.csv', 'daily_20260414.csv']:\n    try:\n        df = pd.read_csv(f'/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/tushare_raw/{f}', nrows=3)\n        print(f'{f}: {len(df)} cols, sample: {list(df.columns[:5])}')\n        print(df.head(1).to_string())\n    except Except