{"type":"message","id":"655f8b84","parentId":"1ddd1474","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:04:35.021Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The CSV files do contain data! daily_20260414.csv has 5496 rows and SH600000/SH600519 data is there. But the D.features() query returned empty for SZ000001 on 04/14.\n\nWait - the D.features() query used `'SZ000001'` but the CSV contains `'SH600000'` and `'SH600519'`. Let me check if SZ000001 is actually in the file. The symbol in the CSV is the raw Tushare format (e.g., `SH600000`) but Qlib uses a different format (e.g., `SH600000` without the exchange prefix?).Let me check what the qlib instruments look like.","thinkingSignature":"5484d32ef46b666fca2b8e512e335804f034b91cf379e2e717ea3e4347d70a0e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m637le8cp2oj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"/usr/bin/python3 -c \"\nimport pandas as pd\ndf = pd.read_csv('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/tushare_raw/daily_20260414.csv')\n# 找 SZ000001\nsz = df[df['symbol'].str.contains('SZ000001', na=False)]\nprint('SZ000001 in CSV:', len(sz))\nif len(sz) == 0:\n    # 检查北京证券交易所的股票\n    bj = df[df['symbol'].str.startswith('BJ', na=False)]\n    print('BJ stocks:', len(bj), bj['symbol'].unique()[:5])\n    # 找上海股票\n    sh = df[df['symbol'].str.startswith('SH', na=False)]\n    print('SH stocks total:', len(sh), 'SH600000 in CSV:', 'SH600000' in df['symbol'].values)\n    print('First 5 SH:', sh['symbol'].head(5).tolist())\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":76471,"output":386,"cacheRead":35571,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112428,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776171863748,"responseId":"062d6e5be7eeb77248ee9dd9db415f18"}}
