{"type":"message","id":"0363ef38","parentId":"f12cf1b0","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:05:35.233Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so `dump_update` has:\n- `--data_path`: Path to the CSV files\n- `--qlib_dir`: Path to the Qlib data directory\n- `--freq`: Default 'day'\n- `--date_field_name`: Default 'date'\n- `--file_suffix`: Default '.csv'\n- `--symbol_field_name`: Default 'symbol'\n- `--include_fields`: To specify which columns to include\n\nNow let me look at the tushare_to_qlib_update.py to see what the actual dump_update command was. From the earlier log:```\n命令: /Library/Developer/CommandLineTools/usr/bin/python3 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/qlib/scripts/dump_bin.py dump_update --data_path /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/tushare_raw --qlib_dir ...\n\n\n```\n\nIt didn't show the full command. Let me look at the Python code more carefully to see what the actual command was. The CSV files have date and symbol columns, which match the defaults, but the issue might be with how the symbol is formatted. Looking at the CSV, the symbols look like 'SH600000', which should work as qlib instruments. Let me check the dump_bin.py code itself to see what format it actually expects.\n\nActually, I should look at the run_dump_update function to see how the command is constructed and what parameters are being passed.","thinkingSignature":"cedd3f18bb90b7a4aa6b35b9185d070379b42d2a41c3a836ab509c0502526450"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vtzphpvcrcyr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '97,120p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/tushare_to_qlib_update.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":79515,"output":368,"cacheRead":35571,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115454,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"c