{"type":"message","id":"c261236d","parentId":"f037faed","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:06:49.310Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The symbols are like `920000.BJ`, `920001.BJ`, etc. But in qlib instruments, the format is like `BJ920000` (exchange prefix + code). So the symbol format in the CSV (`920000.BJ`) doesn't match the qlib format (`BJ920000`).This is the root cause! The dump_update is reading the CSV with `symbol=920000.BJ`, but qlib's instrument list only has `BJ920000`, so there's a mismatch and no data gets written.\n\nNow I need to understand why the earlier dates (04/07-04/10) DID get written to qlib. Let me check what the old CSV looked like.","thinkingSignature":"6e73e7d5767e97c646c023bc93ad0657016de6abd01b448e9466e6afb7f6970d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xicdbf6q559n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -3 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/tushare_raw/daily_20260410.csv 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\n# Check what format the original a_stock_daily_converted.csv uses\nhead -3 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/tushare_a_all/a_stock_daily_converted.csv 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":82879,"output":271,"cacheRead":35571,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":118721,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776172000368,"responseId":"062d6ee4b3f5202e72ba8e070e901227"}}
