ugh roughly index 879, which should give me data from early 2019 through about 2022 or 2023. But the stock price values seem way too large to be in yuan, so I'm clearly misinterpreting something fundamental about this data format.","thinkingSignature":"8b9e44eacc865cf5682fa2a5e1f59d6e50d31de41453c5d945a723f4ee22becf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_00uc6mer7ziz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"/usr/bin/python3 -c \"\nimport numpy as np\n\nbin_path = '/Users/ling/.qlib/qlib_data/cn_data_long_2015_2026_180/features/SH600000/close.day.bin'\ndata = np.frombuffer(open(bin_path, 'rb').read(), dtype=np.float32)\nn = len(data) // 2\n\n# Read calendar\ncal = []\nwith open('/Users/ling/.qlib/qlib_data/cn_data_long_2015_2026_180/calendars/day.txt') as f:\n    for line in f:\n        cal.append(line.strip())\n\n# Show records around index 875 (near end of file)\nprint('Records around index 870-880:')\nfor i in range(max(0, 870), min(n, 880)):\n    idx = int(data[2*i])\n    d = cal[idx] if idx < len(cal) else f'idx={idx}>len'\n    print(f'  [{idx:4d}] {d}: close={data[2*i+1]:.4f}')\n\n# Find what calendar index corresponds to 2026-04-08\ntarget = '2026-04-08'\ntry:\n    target_idx = cal.index(target)\n    print(f'\\\\n2026-04-08 is at calendar index: {target_idx}')\n    print(f'Expected number of records for 2019-01-02 to 2026-04-08: {target_idx + 1}')\n    print(f'Actual number of records in file: {n}')\nexcept:\n    print(f'{target} not found in calendar')\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":93909,"output":867,"cacheRead":35571,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":130347,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776172224171,"responseId":"062d6fc4a60fc95f36a57f39fd2e6f8c"}}
