{"type":"message","id":"6d62b62c","parentId":"3060f2cc","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:11:50.522Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait - it's saying the file doesn't exist! But earlier we confirmed it exists with `ls`. Let me check again.\n\nOh wait, I see the issue. When running via exec, the `qlib/scripts/dump_bin.py` path doesn't exist from the current working directory. But when running via the `cron_python.sh` wrapper, the Python binary resolves the path correctly.Actually wait, `/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/qlib/scripts/dump_bin.py` DOES exist (we confirmed earlier with `ls`). The issue might be that `sys.executable` is pointing to a different Python version.\n\nLet me re-check. In my exec commands, I'm using `/usr/bin/python3` which is Python 3.9 (system Python). The cron_python.sh uses a different Python. \n\nSo the dump_bin.py might have a hashbang pointing to a non-standard Python path, which is why it's not being found when I run it directly.","thinkingSignature":"4c4ba7211710f9e9c04d89906b4d7e191296a9b2ad812a7172fc3b728e46c709"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_eoe14xmgqxae_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -3 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/qlib/scripts/dump_bin.py\necho \"---\"\nwhich python3 2>/dev/null\nls -la /usr/bin/python3 /usr/local/bin/python3 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":97589,"output":281,"cacheRead":35571,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":133441,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776172300318,"responseId":"062d701010b2a125834d79a348911eb8"}}
