{"type":"compaction","id":"970e697c","parentId":"fc4d13dd","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:14:38.851Z","summary":"## Summary\n\n### Conversation Overview\n\nThe conversation contains three distinct threads:\n\n1. **Fixing the ML prediction pipeline** (primary focus) — `generate_extended_predictions.py` crashes with SIGKILL; root cause is memory exhaustion from loading all 5499 stocks × years of data via Qlib DatasetH handler; several corrective scripts were written and tested\n2. **屈原列传** — User asked about Qu Yuan's biography (off-topic cultural question, fully answered)\n3. **Quant panel question** — User asked why 9 paper trading accounts exist but only 4 are shown in the report\n\n---\n\n## Goal\nFix the ML prediction generation pipeline so `ml_predictions_live_latest.csv` extends from 2026-04-03 through the latest available Qlib data (2026-04-10), enabling the breadth paper trading accounts to resume signal generation. Also set up a daily cron job to prevent the same breakage after future holidays.\n\n---\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Mac mini has ~8GB RAM total; Qlib's full DatasetH (5499 stocks × 158 features × 11 years) causes SIGKILL/OOM\n- `tushare_to_qlib_update.py` has NO cron entry — manually run only\n- Qlib features are stored in `.day.bin` binary format (not CSV)\n- Available Qlib fields: `[$close, $open, $high, $low, $volume]` only (Alpha158 derived features computed on-the-fly)\n- `generate_extended_predictions.py` uses `DatasetH` + `Alpha158` handler which preloads ALL data into RAM — incompatible with memory constraints\n- Python 3.9 (system) uses `spawn` multiprocessing method; Python 3.14 (user install) uses `fork`; `freeze_support()` guard needed\n- Qlib calendar for 2026: trading days are 04-01, 04-02, 04-03, 04-07, 04-08, 04-09, 04-10 (清明休市 04-04~04-06); today 04-14 is Monday (trading day) but data not yet downloaded\n- Tushare `download_tushare_update.log` shows last update was 2026-04-13 at 16:03 reaching 2026-04-10; today's 04-14 data not yet in Tushare\n\n---\n\n## Progress\n\n### Done\n- [x] **Identified root cause**: After Qingming Festival (04/04–04/06), `tushare_to_qlib_update.py` was never executed. Tushare data updated to 2026-04-10 on April 13 at 16:03, but Qlib conversion pipeline was skipped, leaving Qlib data stuck at 2026-04-03\n- [x] **Verified Qlib data**: Confirmed Qlib data directory (`~/.qlib/qlib_data/cn_data_long_2015_2026_180/`) already extends to 2026-04-10 via the `universe180.txt` file modified 2026-04-13 at 00:57; `tushare_to_qlib_update.py` reports \"无新日期需要更新\" confirming Qlib is current\n- [x] **Confirmed SIGKILL root cause**: `generate_extended_predictions.py` loads successfully (107s) but is killed by system OOM killer during `model.fit(dataset)` — DatasetH with Alpha158 handler creates ~124M+ row DataFrame exceeding available RAM\n- [x] **Identified column mismatch bug**: In batch loading, `df.columns = [\"symbol\", \"date\"] + [f.replace(\"$\",\"\") for f in fields[1:]]` assigns 6 names to 7 columns (missing first field name); fixed by using all 5 fields: `FIELD_NAMES = [f.replace(\"$\",\"\") for f in fields]`\n- [x] **Located all 9 paper trading accounts** from `strategy_performance_panel_latest.json`: 3 active GREEN (Aggressive 18%, Balanced 12%, Defensive 8%), 3 YELLOW/STALE (Alpha55, v4.3 Aggressive, Exit Dual/Tight), 3 breadth accounts (Breadth Aggressive, Breadth Strict OOS, Breadth Small Cap)\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Running `generate_predictions_lite.py`** via `/usr/bin/python3` (system Python 3.9) with `OMP_NUM_THREADS=4` — script is written with `if __name__ == \"__main__\":` guard, corrected column handling, and staged data loading (train: 2019-2020 → test: 2024-2026); process `young-reef` (pid 83462) is currently running\n- [ ] **Second run of `generate_predictions_lite.py`** via process `warm-cedar` (pid 81261) — was writing the corrected version when the user sent the \"屈原列传\" message; that corrected version was subsequently saved and a new exec was issued under `young-reef`\n\n### Blocked\n- Both `generate_extended_predictions.py` and `generate_extended_predictions_lite.py` (original version) crashed with SIGKILL due to OOM — mitigated by using staged data loading in `generate_predictions_lite.py`\n- `cron_python.sh`-invoked Python 3.14 fails with multiprocessing spawn/fork conflict; must use `/usr/bin/python3` (Python 3.9) which requires `if __name__ == '__main__':` guard\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Qlib data conversion is NOT needed**: `tushare_to_qlib_update.py` already successfully ran and Qlib data is current through 2026-04-10; no action needed on that step\n- **Bypass Qlib DatasetH handler**: Instead of fixing `generate_extended_predictions.py`, write a standalone script that uses Qlib's `D.features()` API directly with batched date loading (10-day batches) to avoid loading the full dataset into RAM\n- **Use system Python 3.9**: `/usr/bin/python3` avoids fork/multiprocessing issues seen with Python 3.14\n- **Limit training period**: Load 2019-2020 (2 years) for training, 2024-2026 for testing, with 5499 stocks in `universe180`\n- **Use simplified features**: Load only OHLCV fields from Qlib, compute roc/rsi/vol_ratio features manually\n- **Use float32**: All feature arrays cast to `np.float32` to reduce memory footprint\n- **No new cron added yet**: Cron setup deferred until the prediction generation is confirmed working\n\n---\n\n## Decisions\n- **Decision**: Load Qlib data in two non-overlapping phases (train: 2019-2020, test: 2024-2026) to minimize peak memory by keeping only one phase in memory at a time, with explicit `gc.collect()` between phases\n- **Decision**: Use LightGBM's native API (`lgb.train`, `lgb.Dataset`) rather than Qlib's model wrapper to have fine-grained control over memory management\n- **Decision**: Write new script `generate_predictions_lite.py` to `scripts/` directory rather than modifying the existing broken `generate_extended_predictions.py`\n- **Decision**: For the quant panel question, the 9 accounts are: 3 active D/B/A paper profiles (GREEN), 3 experimental/stale (YELLOW), 3 breadth overlay accounts (signal stale by 11+ days) — the report previously shown only the 3 active D/B/A accounts plus combo_v1 main chain\n\n---\n\n## Next Steps\n\n1. **Poll process `young-reef`** (pid 83462) to check if `generate_predictions_lite.py` completed successfully\n2. **If successful**: Verify `ml_predictions_live_latest.csv` now has dates 2026-04-07 through 2026-04-10 with pred_rank values\n3. **If still OOM**: Further reduce training period to 2020 only, or reduce stock count to top-1000 by volume, or reduce num_boost_round to 50\n4. **Set up daily cron**: Add `cron_python.sh`-style wrapper to run `generate_predictions_lite.py` at 16:30 daily\n5. **Fix signal lag**: Breadth accounts are 11 days stale (signal_date 2026-04-03 vs today 2026-04-14) — once predictions are current, verify breadth overlay refreshes automatically\n\n---\n\n## Critical Context\n\n### Pipeline Data Flow\n```\nTushare daily download (04/13 16:03 → 04/10) ✅\n    ↓\ntushare_to_qlib_update.py (already ran, 04/13 → Qlib 04/10) ✅\n    ↓ [BLOCKED]\ngenerate_extended_predictions.py / generate_predictions_lite.py ❌→🔄\n    ↓\nml_predictions_live_latest.csv (stuck at 04/03, needs 04/07~04/10) 🔄\n```\n\n### File Paths\n- Qlib data: `~/.qlib/q\n\n[Compaction summary truncated to fit budget]\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Decisions\n- **cron 生效时间**: 周一至周五 16:30，每天自动执行\n- **日期自动检测**: 增量起始 = Qlib 最新日期 + 1天，截止 = 当天（16:30 收盘后）\n- **预测截止日期**: Qlib 最新日期（当日收盘后），通过 Python 动态 patch `EXTEND_END` 行后运行 `generate_extended_predictions.py`\n- **dump_bin.py 路径修复**: `PROJECT_ROOT / \"qlib/scripts/dump_bin.py\"` → `PROJECT_ROOT.parent / \"qlib/scripts/dump_bin.py\"`，因 `qlib` 包位于 `quant_projects/qlib/` 而非项目子目录\n- **不过问历史回填**: 仅处理次日增量，不补历史\n\n## Open TODOs\n- 尚未验证 `generate_extended_predictions.py` 能否成功运行（当前 Qlib 已更新至 04/14，但该脚本 `EXTEND_END` 仍为 \"2026-04-11\"，patch 后未实际执行验证）\n- 尚未验证 `run_daily_qlib