{"type":"message","id":"fa0ca12e","parentId":"2f026642","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:38:44.444Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that SH600000 only has 880 records (as we discovered earlier), and index 1759 is out of range. This confirms the Qlib bin data for SH600000 only goes up to calendar index 879 (2022-08-16), NOT up to 2026-04-08. The bin files were corrupted or incomplete.\n\nSo the fundamental issue is: **the Qlib bin feature files don't contain data beyond 2022-08-16 for SH600000 (and likely many other stocks).**\n\nThis is why:\n1. `D.features()` works in Python 3.14 (returns 04/08 data) but the bin files themselves are incomplete\n\n\n2. The bin files were rebuilt incorrectly at some point, yet somehow D.features still manages to retrieve the data\n\nI need to figure out whether D.features is reading from cache, using a different data source, or if the bin files themselves are actually complete and I'm just misinterpreting what I'm seeing.","thinkingSignature":"1e3a5cc358052139b0673fbd7e41aede4b4aaf28bb326f4b4b3db67b6cf9375a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6yp592d9gkgw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 核心问题：SH600000 的 bin 文件只有880条（到2022年）但 D.features 能读到 2026-04-08\n# 这意味着 bin 文件不是 Qlib 读取数据的唯一来源\n# 检查 D.features 到底从哪里读的\n/usr/bin/python3 -c \"\nimport qlib\nfrom pathlib import Path\nqlib.init(provider_uri=str(Path.home() / '.qlib/qlib_data/cn_data_long_2015_2026_180'), region='cn')\n\n# 检查 qlib 内部用的 features 路径\nimport os\nsym = 'SH600000'\nfeat_dir = Path.home() / '.qlib/qlib_data/cn_data_long_2015_2026_180/features' / sym.lower()\nprint('Features dir exists:', feat_dir.exists())\nprint('Bin files:', os.listdir(feat_dir) if feat_dir.exists() else 'N/A')\n\n# 查看 qlib 数据集的配置\nfrom qlib.data import D\nimport qlib as q\nprint('QLib data path:', q.get_data_path())\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":51636,"output":464,"cacheRead":39381,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91481,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173909389,"responseId":"062d76598ba68518a4b98cdfed68041d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"64a618d7","parentId":"fa0ca12e","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:38:45.622Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6yp592d9gkgw_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Features dir exists: True\nBin files: ['close.day.bin', 'low.day.bin', 'high.day.bin', 'volume.day.bin', 'open.day.bin']\nAttributeError: module 'qlib' has no attribute 'get_data_path'\n\n(Command exited with code 1)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":1,"durationMs":1082,"aggregated":"Features dir exists: True\nBin files: ['close.day.bin', 'low.day.bin', 'high.day.bin', 'volume.day.bin', 'open.day.bin']\nAttributeError: module 'qlib' has no attribute 'get_data_path'\n\n(Command exited with code 1)","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776173925603}}
{"type":"message","id":"7719d00a","parentId":"64a618d7","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:39:01.720Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I think I see what's happening now. The `D.features()` in Python 3.14 successfully returns data for 2026-04-08, but the bin files only have 880 records. This is contradictory unless:\n\n1. Qlib 3.14 uses a different reader that's not just reading the bin files directly, OR\n2. The bin files were recently updated but in a different format\n\nWait - actually, I just realized something. When I checked the bin file size:\n- SH600000 close.day.bin: 7044 bytes = 1761 float32 values = 880.5 pairs\n\n\n- But there are actually 1761 calendar entries from 2019-01-02 to 2026-04-14, so if each entry is 12 bytes (4-byte index + 8-byte float), the file should be around 21,132 bytes instead of 7,044. This suggests the bin file isn't storing all calendar entries as I assumed—maybe it's using a different storage format entirely.\n\n- Looking at the float32 values themselves, date_idx=0 maps to 1970-01-01 and date_idx=10 maps to 1970-01-11, which doesn't align with the calendar at all. The file appears to be selecting a subset of dates rather than storing the full range.\n\n- This makes me think D.features might be pulling data from a different source in Python 3.14—possibly a cache, an updated bin format, or another data provider entirely. Let me check what qlib.workflow is actually accessing when it calls D.features.\n\n- I should look at the Python 3.14 environment's site-packages to see if there's a different qlib installation there.","thinkingSignature":"e765aed6869b868936547a9895a2da90deff64839b033af04d752c4a5ece6fca"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aua1q6ry2xnp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 查找 qlib 在 python3.14 中的安装位置\npython3 -c \"import qlib; print(qlib.__file__)\" 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\npython3 -c \"import importlib.util; spec = importlib.util.find_spec('qlib'); print(spec.origin if spec else 'not found')\" 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\n# 查看 qlib 3.14 版本的 bin reading 代码\nfind /Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.14 -name \"*.py\" 2>/dev/null | xargs grep -l \"frombuffer\\|float32\\|day.bin\" 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":52172,"output":533,"cacheRead":39381,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92086,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173925624,"responseId":"062d7669a2b02adf752e974e13ab4c55"}}
