{"type":"message","id":"c7211597","parentId":"3b0d6b2c","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:39:31.558Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the actual format! Line 336: `index = int(np.frombuffer(fp.read(4), dtype=\"<f\")[0])` - the first 4 bytes are a float32 (not uint32). And then lines 357-372 show the data is stored as `<f` (float32) pairs.\n\nLet me re-read the bin file with this correct understanding:\n- First 4 bytes: index as float32\n- Then pairs of (index, value) as float32\n\nWait, let me look more carefully at lines 335-373.","thinkingSignature":"51c3767b1e1ed943838c38371bdc4434a037c84e8b20fea307ddfc2c9ec0e4a8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n9jm2qugnzjb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '330,380p' /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/qlib/qlib/data/storage/file_storage.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":55272,"output":177,"cacheRead":39381,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94830,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173965719,"responseId":"062d769295db98e7e2c07b8b293621b1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2ceadebb","parentId":"c7211597","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:39:31.717Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n9jm2qugnzjb_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"@property\n    def start_index(self) -> Union[int, None]:\n        if not self.uri.exists():\n            return None\n        with self.uri.open(\"rb\") as fp:\n            index = int(np.frombuffer(fp.read(4), dtype=\"<f\")[0])\n        return index\n\n    @property\n    def end_index(self) -> Union[int, None]:\n        if not self.uri.exists():\n            return None\n        # The next  data appending index point will be  `end_index + 1`\n        return self.start_index + len(self) - 1\n\n    def __getitem__(self, i: Union[int, slice]) -> Union[Tuple[int, float], pd.Series]:\n        if not self.uri.exists():\n            if isinstance(i, int):\n                return None, None\n            elif isinstance(i, slice):\n                return pd.Series(dtype=np.float32)\n            else:\n                raise TypeError(f\"type(i) = {type(i)}\")\n\n        storage_start_index = self.start_index\n        storage_end_index = self.end_index\n        with self.uri.open(\"rb\") as fp:\n            if isinstance(i, int):\n                if storage_start_index > i:\n                    raise IndexError(f\"{i}: start index is {storage_start_index}\")\n                fp.seek(4 * (i - storage_start_index) + 4)\n                return i, struct.unpack(\"f\", fp.read(4))[0]\n            elif isinstance(i, slice):\n                start_index = storage_start_index if i.start is None else i.start\n                end_index = storage_end_index if i.stop is None else i.stop - 1\n                si = max(start_index, storage_start_index)\n                if si > end_index:\n                    return pd.Series(dtype=np.float32)\n                fp.seek(4 * (si - storage_start_index) + 4)\n                # read n bytes\n                count = end_index - si + 1\n                data = np.frombuffer(fp.read(4 * count), dtype=\"<f\")\n                return pd.Series(data, index=pd.RangeIndex(si, si + len(data)))\n            else:\n                raise TypeError(f\"type(i) = {type(i)}\")\n\n    def __len__(self) -> int:\n        self.check()\n        return self.uri.stat().st_size // 4 - 1"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":37,"aggregated":"@property\n    def start_index(self) -> Union[int, None]:\n        if not self.uri.exists():\n            return None\n        with self.uri.open(\"rb\") as fp:\n            index = int(np.frombuffer(fp.read(4), dtype=\"<f\")[0])\n        return index\n\n    @property\n    def end_index(self) -> Union[int, None]:\n        if not self.uri.exists():\n            return None\n        # The next  data appending index point will be  `end_index + 1`\n        return self.start_index + len(self) - 1\n\n    def __getitem__(self, i: Union[int, slice]) -> Union[Tuple[int, float], pd.Series]:\n        if not self.uri.exists():\n            if isinstance(i, int):\n                return None, None\n            elif isinstance(i, slice):\n                return pd.Series(dtype=np.float32)\n            else:\n                raise TypeError(f\"type(i) = {type(i)}\")\n\n        storage_start_index = self.start_index\n        storage_end_index = self.end_index\n        with self.uri.open(\"rb\") as fp:\n            if isinstance(i, int):\n                if storage_start_index > i:\n                    raise IndexError(f\"{i}: start index is {storage_start_index}\")\n                fp.seek(4 * (i - storage_start_index) + 4)\n                return i, struct.unpack(\"f\", fp.read(4))[0]\n            elif isinstance(i, slice):\n                start_index = storage_start_index if i.start is None else i.start\n                end_index = storage_end_index if i.stop is None else i.stop - 1\n                si = max(start_index, storage_start_index)\n                if si > end_index:\n                    return pd.Series(dtype=np.float32)\n                fp.seek(4 * (si - storage_start_index) + 4)\n                # read n bytes\n                count = end_index - si + 1\n                data = np.frombuffer(fp.read(4 * count), dtype=\"<f\")\n                return pd.Series(data, index=pd.RangeIndex(si, si + len(data)))\n            else:\n                raise TypeError(f\"type(i) = {type(i)}\")\n\n    def __len__(self) -> int:\n        self.check()\n        return self.uri.stat().st_size // 4 - 1","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776173971692}}
{"type":"message","id":"62f331dc","parentId":"2ceadebb","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:39:48.584Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the bin format perfectly:\n1. File size = 4 bytes (header) + 4 * N bytes (data), where N = number of records\n2. Header (first 4 bytes): the starting calendar index as float32\n3. Data: N float32 values, one per calendar entry (from start_index to start_index+N-1)\n\nSo the bin file stores:\n- First 4 bytes: start_index (as float32)\n- Then N float32 values, one for each calendar day from start_index to start_index+N-1\n\nThe bin file does NOT store the index alongside each value! The index is implied by position.\n\n\nLet me verify this with SH600000 close prices. With 7044 bytes total, that gives me 1760 float32 values after the 4-byte header. Since the first calendar entry is 2019-01-02 at index 0, the file should contain prices from index 0 through index 1759, which corresponds to 2026-04-08. But the file only has 880 records, meaning it actually spans from index 0 to 879 (ending around 2022-08-16), so it appears to be incomplete.\n\nNow I'm puzzled because D.features is somehow returning data for 2026-04-08 even though the bin file only goes up to 2022-08-16. Let me check if there's a cache mechanism that might be storing the complete dataset.","thinkingSignature":"33ddd2baf8f292926725a6494923e4a372b43fc1b79cd4a70ff969a6a2939f9a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bhff1uya5pim_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 读取 bin 文件正确的格式\n/usr/bin/python3 -c \"\nimport numpy as np\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nbin_path = Path.home() / '.qlib/qlib_data/cn_data_long_2015_2026_180/features/SH600000/close.day.bin'\nwith open(bin_path, 'rb') as f:\n    data = f.read()\n\n# 格式: 前4字节=float32(start_index), 之后每4字节一个float32值\nn_total = len(data) // 4 - 1  #减去header\nstart_idx = int(np.frombuffer(data[:4], dtype='<f')[0])\nvalues = np.frombuffer(data[4:], dtype='<f')\n\nprint(f'File size: {len(data)} bytes')\nprint(f'Start index: {start_idx} (calendar day {start_idx})')\nprint(f'Number of values: {len(values)}')\nprint(f'End index: {start_idx + len(values) - 1}')\n\n# 读日历\nwith open(Path.home() / '.qlib/qlib_data/cn_data_long_2015_2026_180/calendars/day.txt') as f:\n    cal = [l.strip() for l in f]\n\nprint(f'Calendar day for start_idx={start_idx}: {cal[start_idx]}')\nprint(f'Calendar day for end_idx={start_idx + len(values) - 1}: {cal[start_idx + len(values) - 1]}')\nprint()\nprint('Last 5 values:')\nfor i in range(max(0, len(values)-5), len(values)):\n    cal_idx = start_idx + i\n    print(f'  [{cal_idx}] {cal[cal_idx]}: {values[i]:.4f}')\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":55945,"output":706,"cacheRead":39381,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96032,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173971719,"responseId":"062d769785ee15be7b30ba84722dc1d7"}}
{"type":"message","id":"658a8fd5","parentId":"62f331dc","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:39:48.753Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bhff1uya5pim_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"File size: 7044 bytes\nStart index: 0 (calendar day 0)\nNumber of values: 1760\nEnd index: 1759\nCalendar day for start_idx=0: 2019-01-02\nCalendar day for end_idx=1759: 2026-04-08\n\nLast 5 values:\n  [1755] 2026-04-01: 10.2400\n  [1756] 2026-04-02: 10.2500\n  [1757] 2026-04-03: 10.1200\n  [1758] 2026-04-07: 9.8600\n  [1759] 2026-04-08: 10.0500"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":68,"aggregated":"File size: 7044 bytes\nStart index: 0 (calendar day 0)\nNumber of values: 1760\nEnd index: 1759\nCalendar day for start_idx=0: 2019-01-02\nCalendar day for end_idx=1759: 2026-04-08\n\nLast 5 values:\n  [1755] 2026-04-01: 10.2400\n  [1756] 2026-04-02: 10.2500\n  [1757] 2026-04-03: 10.1200\n  [1758] 2026-04-07: 9.8600\n  [1759] 2026-04-08: 10.0500","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776173988734}}
{"type":"message","id":"33932c49","parentId":"658a8fd5","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:40:01.806Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand! The bin format is:\n- First 4 bytes: start_index as float32\n- Remaining: N float32 values, one per calendar day\n\nSo the file DOES contain data up to 2026-04-08 (calendar index 1759). My earlier reading was wrong because I was reading (index, value) pairs when it's actually just sequential values with an implicit index.\n\nThe Qlib bin file for SH600000 contains 1760 records covering 2019-01-02 to 2026-04-08. But the latest trading day is 2026-04-14 (calendar index 1764). So the bin file is missing data for 04-09, 04-10, 04-13, 04-14.\n\n\nThe bin file is incomplete—it's missing the most recent four trading days. Let me check what the calendar says about those dates.","thinkingSignature":"19d9289813d4443a67575b4f011b4482dbb69430722860dbc831e2a9e4de9b6c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a5ns5ts54u7m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"/usr/bin/python3 -c \"\nimport numpy as np\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# 检查所有股票的 bin 文件是否都完整\nwith open(Path.home() / '.qlib/qlib_data/cn_data_long_2015_2026_180/calendars/day.txt') as f:\n    cal = [l.strip() for l in f]\nn_cal = len(cal)\nlast_cal_idx = n_cal - 1\nprint(f'Calendar: {cal[0]} ~ {cal[-1]}, {n_cal} days')\nprint(f'Last calendar index: {last_cal_idx} = {cal[last_cal_idx]}')\n\n# 检查最后几个 bin 文件的状态\nimport os\nfeat_dir = Path.home() / '.qlib/qlib_data/cn_data_long_2015_2026_180/features'\nsamples = ['SH600000', 'SZ000001', 'SH600519']\nfor sym in samples:\n    sym_dir = feat_dir / sym.lower()\n    close_bin = sym_dir / 'close.day.bin'\n    if close_bin.exists():\n        size = close_bin.stat().st_size\n        n_vals = size // 4 - 1\n        start_idx = 0  # assume start from 0\n        with open(close_bin, 'rb') as f:\n            start_idx = int(np.frombuffer(f.read(4), dtype='<f')[0])\n        end_idx = start_idx + n_vals - 1\n        print(f'{sym}: size={size}, values={n_vals}, start_idx={start_idx}, end_idx={end_idx}')\n        print(f'  last date: {cal[end_idx] if end_idx < n_cal else \\\"OUT OF RANGE\\\"}')\n    else:\n        print(f'{sym}: bin not found')\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":56833,"output":592,"cacheRead":39381,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96806,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173988755,"responseId":"062d76a8a57a0ccaa3c7dce574e48598"}}
