{"type":"message","id":"7b984b92","parentId":"df9dd77a","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:40:39.511Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the raw CSV files DO have data for 04-09, 04-10, 04-13, and 04-14. But the Qlib bin files only have data up to 04-08.\n\nThe `dump_update` script is NOT working correctly for these new dates. Let me run it manually and see what happens.\n\nBut first, let me check the `tushare_to_qlib_update.py` script more carefully to understand what it does.\n\nActually, I think the core problem might be simpler - the `dump_update` command is receiving the CSV directory but the CSV files for the new dates weren't included in the update because the script found no \"new dates\" to update (the calendar already had those dates listed but the bin files were not updated).\n \nNow I see the real issue - `dump_update` is only scanning the CSV directory without specifying which dates to process, so it should pick up all the CSV files including the new ones. The calendar already contains those dates, so when `dump_update` runs, it should regenerate the bin files for those dates. But something's going wrong with the actual update process.\n\nLet me trace through what dates the update script is actually checking for. It looks for the latest date in the calendar, then looks for CSV files newer than that, but if the calendar already includes dates that haven't been written to the bin files yet, there's a mismatch between what the calendar says exists and what's actually been processed.","thinkingSignature":"9e72e9f5c75f68ad7ad40f8a7bdc1116d04fdb209c42f7e3a8c7bf82b62a394d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ipmnqyslhex9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"latest_date\\|new.*date\\|csv.*date\\|start.*end\\|check.*qlib\\|find.*new\" \\\n  /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/tushare_to_qlib_update.py 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","pr