{"type":"message","id":"057f065f","parentId":"deface42","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:43:57.823Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I need to think about this more carefully. The bin file format is:\n- 4 bytes: start_index (float32)\n- N values: float32 values, one per calendar day from start_index to start_index+N-1\n\nSo if I have 1760 values covering indices 0~1759, and I want to add data for indices 1760~1763 (04-09~04-14), I just append 4 float32 values to the file. The start_index in the header remains 0.\n\nMy current code does `arr.tofile(f)` which appends the new values to the existing file. \n\nThis should work! Let me test it. But I'm realizing there might be an issue with the append logic—when I reopen the file in append mode, I need to make sure I'm reading the existing data correctly first to verify the start_index before adding new values.\n\nActually, I see the problem now. The script checks if `n_existing >= N_CAL` to see if the bin is already complete, but that's not the right condition. The existing file has 1760 values spanning indices 0~1759, and I need to append for indices 1760~1763. If N_CAL is 1764, then the condition `1760 >= 1764` fails, so it correctly tries to append. But the new values should only cover the missing indices, not reappend data that already exists. The condition `n_existing >= N_CAL` is wrong since N_CAL represents the total calendar length (1764), not the end index. What I actually need is to check if `n_existing >= N_CAL`, which would mean the file already has all values through the final calendar date. The bin files end at index 1759 (04-08) while the calendar runs through index 1763 (04-14), so I need to append for indices 1760-1763. My condition is off because `n_existing >= N_CAL` (1760 >= 1764) is False, meaning the script will attempt to append—but that's actually checking the wrong threshold since N_CAL should represent the total number of entries, not the index value itself. So the condition fails correctly and we attempt to append. But there's a logic error in the loop: after appending, `n_existing` still equals 1760 on the next iteration, so we'd try to append again for each missing date. I need to update `n_existing` after appending to prevent re-appending data we just added.\n\nActually, I'm realizing each field (close, open, high, low, volume) gets processed independently with its own append, so this double-appending would happen for every field. Let me refactor the approach to make it cleaner and avoid these bugs.\n\nWriting corrected script...","thinkingSignature":"a212b5dec75d869f9ed7b1414e6cd7fd4a663cd00dceffd91188d8055e8b4ea7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bbqkwy0koqv0_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/append_missing_qlib_bins.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\n追加 Qlib bin 缺失数据（04-09~04-14）\nbin 文件只有到04-08，日历已有04-14，修复不一致\n\"\"\"\nimport sys\nimport warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nQLIB_DATA_DIR = Path.home() / '.qlib/qlib_data/cn_data_long_2015_2026_180'\nUNIVERSE_FILE = QLIB_DATA_DIR / 'instruments' / 'universe180.txt'\nCAL_FILE = QLIB_DATA_DIR / 'calendars' / 'day.txt'\nRAW_DIR = Path('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/tushare_raw')\n\nFIELDS = ['close', 'open', 'high', 'low', 'volume']\n\nwith open(CAL_FILE) as f:\n    CAL = [l.strip() for l in f]\nN_CAL = len(CAL)\nMISSING_DATES = CAL[1760:]  # 04-09, 04-10, 04-13, 04-14\nMISSING_COUNT = len(MISSING_DATES)\n\nprint(f\"日历: {CAL[0]} ~ {CAL[-1]}, 共{N_CAL}天\")\nprint(f\"缺失: {MISSING_DATES} ({MISSING_COUNT}天)\")\n\nwith open(UNIVERSE_FILE) as f:\n    instruments = [l.strip() for l in f if l.strip() and not l.startswith('#')]\nprint(f\"Universe: {len(instruments)} 只股票\")\n\n# 加载 CSV 数据\nprint(\"\\n加载 CSV...\")\nall_data = {}\nfor date_str in MISSING_DATES:\n    csv_file = RAW_DIR / f\"daily_{date_str.replace('-','')}.csv\"\n    if not csv_file.exists():\n        print(f\"  {date_str}: CSV NOT FOUND\")\n        continue\n    df = pd.read_csv(csv_file)\n    data_dict = {}\n    for _, row in df.iterrows():\n        data_dict[row['symbol']] = {\n            'close':  float(row['close']),\n            'open':   float(row['open']),\n            'high':   float(row['high']),\n            'low':    float(row['low']),\n            'volume': float(row['volume']),\n        }\n    all_data[date_str] = data_dict\n    print(f\"  {date_str}: {len(data_dict)} 只股票 ✅\")\n\nprint(f\"\\n开始追加 ({MISSING_COUNT} 天 × {len(instruments)} 只)...\")\n\nok = 0\nskip = 0\nerrors = []\n\nfor i, sym in enumerate(instruments):\n    sym_dir = QLIB_DATA_DIR / 'features' / sym.lower()\n    if not sym_dir.exists():\n        skip += 1\n        continue\n\n    # 读取每个 field 的 bin，追加缺失值\n    for fld in FIELDS:\n        bin_path = sym_dir / f'{fld}.day.bin'\n        if not bin_path.exists():\n            continue\n\n        with open(bin_path, 'rb') as f:\n            existing = f.read()\n\n        n_existing = len(existing) // 4 - 1\n\n        # 如果已有全部日历值，跳过\n        if n_existing >= N_CAL:\n            continue\n\n        # 构建缺失值数组\n        new_arr = np.array([\n            float(all_data.get(d, {}).get(sym, {}).get(fld, np.nan))\n            if d in all_data else np.nan\n            for d in MISSING_DATES\n        ], dtype='<f')\n\n        # 追加到 bin 文件\n        with open(bin_path, 'ab') as f:\n            new_arr.tofile(f)\n\n    ok += 1\n    if (i + 1) % 1000 == 0:\n        print(f\"  {i+1}/{len(instruments)} ...\")\n\nprint(f\"\\n完成: ok={ok}, skip(no_dir)={skip}, errors={len(errors)}\")\nif errors:\n    for e in errors[:5]:\n        print(f\"  ERROR: {e}\")\n\n# 验证\nsym = instruments[0]\nsym_dir = QLIB_DATA_DIR / 'features' / sym.lower()\nwith open(sym_dir / 'close.day.bin', 'rb') as f:\n    data = f.read()\nn_vals = len(data) // 4 - 1\nstart_idx = int(np.frombuffer(data[:4], dtype='<f')[0])\nend_idx = start_idx + n_vals - 1\nvalues = np.frombuffer(data[4:], dtype='<f')\nprint(f\"\\n验证 {sym}: {n_vals} values, last={CAL[end_idx] if end_idx < N_CAL else 'OUT OF RANGE'}\")\nprint(f\"最后4值: {values[-4:]}\")\nprint(f\"对应: {[CAL[start_idx + n_vals - 4 + i] for i in range(4)]}\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69079,"output":1746,"cacheRead":39381,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110206,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776174201807,"responseId":"062d777e21d1829150a224b44f650c33"}}
