{"type":"message","id":"d4ab626c","parentId":"04413885","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:46:21.163Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The CSV symbols are:\n- BJ stocks: `920000.BJ` (dot notation)\n- SH stocks: `SH600000`\n- SZ stocks: `SZ000001`\n\nSo my normalization to uppercase gives `920000.BJ` → `920000.BJ` (uppercase), but then `sym_to_dir('920000.BJ')` would fail since it only handles `BJ` prefix (not `BJ` suffix).\n\nI need to handle both notations. Let me update `sym_to_dir` to handle:\n- `920000.BJ` → `920000.bj`\n- `SH600000` → `sh600000`\n\n\n- `SZ000001` → `sz000001`\n\nAnd make sure the conversion from CSV to normalized form is correct: `920000.BJ` → `BJ920000` → `920000.bj`.\n\nWriting symbol normalization logic...","thinkingSignature":"21478214e9cd46dae71a5b3e2e1764f90197a5fab89f2705406d7d922b0ec68a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jzql9q4ktrzl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"/usr/bin/python3 << 'EOF'\n# Test symbol conversion\ndef normalize_symbol(sym):\n    \"\"\"Normalize CSV symbol to Qlib format\"\"\"\n    sym = sym.upper().strip()\n    # Handle 920000.BJ format\n    if '.' in sym:\n        parts = sym.split('.')\n        if len(parts) == 2 and parts[1] == 'BJ':\n            return 'BJ' + parts[0]\n        return sym\n    return sym\n\ntest = ['920000.BJ', 'SH600000', 'SZ000001', 'BJ920000', '  sh600000  ']\nfor s in test:\n    print(f'{s!r} -> {normalize_symbol(s)}')\nEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":76778,"output":359,"cacheRead":39381,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116518,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776174371540,"responseId":"062d782722a1a0ee811b11da282552f7"}}
