{"type":"message","id":"1378ed7b","parentId":"d106e61f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:50:17.457Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the bug! The `v3.py` script loads CSV symbols as-is (without normalization), so `'920000.BJ'` stays as `'920000.BJ'`. But the instruments list has `'BJ920000'`. Then `sym_to_dir('BJ920000')` gives `'920000.bj'` which matches the feature directory, but the lookup `all_data['2026-04-09']['BJ920000']` fails because the key is `'920000.BJ'`.\n\nI need to add `normalize_symbol` to the CSV loading in v3.py. Let me fix this.\n\nActually wait, I also need to check the instruments. \n\nThe universe file has `'BJ920000'` (uppercase, no dot) while CSV has `'920000.BJ'`, so when I try to look up the symbol using the instruments list format, it won't match the CSV keys. This is the same bug that plagued the append script. The fix is to add `normalize_symbol` to the CSV loading step in v3.py.\n\nSince the CSV data has about 5491 rows for 2026-04-09, iterating through all of them would be slow, but I can't pre-compute the normalized mapping either since the loop is necessary. Let me add `normalize_symbol` to v3.py and test it.","thinkingSignature":"eafb20d2d6229b07cacf5a3edab93fd5a3b0c8bd4baae8cd6e2e57ec26c77a79"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1uplxaveue3m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"normalize_symbol\\|for _, row in df.iterrows\\|data_dict\\[sym\\]\" \\\n  /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_predictions_lite_v3.py 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":90960,"output":354,"cacheRead":35569,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":126883,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776178205661,"responseId":"062d871e2857d69ee54024542dfa868c"}}
