{"type":"message","id":"7c6b5daa","parentId":"66b46669","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:52:31.819Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the `run_daily_qlib_pipeline.sh` imports from `append_missing_qlib_bins` which has `if __name__ == '__main__'` guard and also does CSV loading at module load time. That's problematic. Let me simplify.Actually, the append_missing_qlib_bins script doesn't have an `if __name__ == '__main__'` guard - it runs the append at module import time. That's dangerous for the cron script. Let me just remove that part and keep it simple.Actually, let me reconsider. The `append_missing_qlib_bins` script was designed to be run standalone. When imported, it runs the append. But I should make it a proper module with a main guard. Let me fix the pipeline script instead to not import from it, but instead call the tushare_to_qlib_update which handles the dump_update.\n\n\nActually, the real issue is that `tushare_to_qlib_update.py` has its own safeguards - it checks if Qlib is already current and skips the dump if nothing new is needed. So maybe I don't need the extra append step at all. Let me just strip down the pipeline to call the update script and be done with it.\n\nThough I'm noticing the cron wrapper itself might be fragile - it's doing inline Python to calculate the next day, which could break. I should make the wrapper more robust.","thinkingSignature":"b62586e563e614aec80932a8a927145e49c744fef66469fddf3fb8f05b20ffef"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jolqzrih8ohj_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_daily_qlib_pipeline.sh","content":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# 每日 Qlib 管道（彻底方案）\n# 周一~周五 16:30 执行\n# 用 generate_predictions_lite_v3.py 直接读 bin，避免 DatasetH OOM\nset -euo pipefail\n\nROOT=\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system\"\nPYTHON=\"/usr/bin/python3\"\nLOG=\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/logs/daily_qlib_pipeline.log\"\n\nlog() { echo \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] $*\" | tee -a \"$LOG\"; }\n\ncd \"$ROOT\"\nlog \"=== 每日 Qlib 管道开始 ===\"\n\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\n\n# Step 1: Tushare → Qlib 增量更新\nlog \"[Step1] Tushare下载...\"\n$PYTHON scripts/tushare_to_qlib_update.py --start \"2026-04-01\" --end \"$TODAY\" >> \"$LOG\" 2>&1 || true\nlog \"[Step1] 完成\"\n\n# Step 2: 生成预测（lite v3 直接读 bin，不会 OOM）\nlog \"[Step2] 生成预测...\"\n$PYTHON scripts/generate_predictions_lite_v3.py >> \"$LOG\" 2>&1 || true\nlog \"[Step2] 完成\"\n\n# 验证\nif [[ -f \"$ROOT/ml_predictions_live_latest.csv\" ]]; then\n    RESULT=$($PYTHON -c \"\nimport pandas as pd, sys\ndf = pd.read_csv('$ROOT/ml_predictions_live_latest.csv')\nprint(f'{len(df)} 条，最新 {df[\\\"date\\\"].max()}')\n\" 2>/dev/null)\n    log \"结果: $RESULT\"\nfi\n\nlog \"=== 管道完成 ===\"\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":98173,"output":732,"cacheRead":35569,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134474,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776178333549,"responseId":"062d879ddb32f701cbd3fa0d8a8ad14a"}}
