{"type":"message","id":"b859cd0c","parentId":"da259113","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:54:31.049Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-14 22:54:27 GMT+8] Feishu[coding-agent] DM | 张玲 (ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae) [msg:om_x100b52d11ce3e4a0b207c8d458a23dd]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b52d11ce3e4a0b207c8d458a23dd\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae\",\n  \"sender\": \"张玲\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-04-14 22:54 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"张玲 (ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae\",\n  \"name\": \"张玲\"\n}\n```\n\n现在需要修复模拟盘混乱的问题，为什么要下线的纸盘收益却最好？"}],"timestamp":1776178471034}}
{"type":"message","id":"83170a9c","parentId":"b859cd0c","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:54:57.699Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about a problem with the paper trading accounts - some accounts that should be offline/winding down are showing the best returns, which doesn't make sense. This is a question about the quant panel / paper trading system.\n\nLet me think about what could cause this. The user is referring to \"模拟盘混乱的问题\" (paper trading chaos) and \"下线的纸盘收益却最好\" (offline paper trading accounts showing the best returns).\n\nFrom our conversation history, I know there are 9 paper trading accounts:\n- 3 active (GREEN): Aggressive 18%, Balanced 12%, Defensive 8%\n- 3 YELLOW/STALE: Alpha55, v4.3 Aggressive, Exit Dual/Tight  \n\n\n- 3 breadth accounts: Breadth Aggressive, Breadth Strict OOS, Breadth Small Cap\n\nThe panel report likely shows the breadth accounts as stale since they're not generating fresh signals. The question is why offline accounts would show returns at all - they shouldn't be making new trades, so any returns would come from existing holdings that haven't been closed out yet. If these accounts are closed or frozen but the holdings have persisted, they'd show returns based on position value changes rather than active trading decisions.\n\nThe real issue might be survivorship bias - closed accounts with failed stocks that got delisted would show huge losses or be zeroed out, while accounts with stocks that survived and rallied would show gains. Looking at the timestamps, the breadth accounts went stale on 04-03 and haven't updated since, so they're frozen in time while the active accounts continued trading through 04-14. That means the breadth accounts would be showing their last known portfolio state, which could look artificially good or bad depending on what positions they happened to hold at that point.\n\nI need to check the strategy performance data and the cron job that generates the panel report to see how the breadth overlay is actually pulling signals and whether there's a disconnect between what's stale and what's being reported.","thinkingSignature":"64d2a671cb1288617dbd8306255ce8880c0b16eaeb6b85d26ac1b5cabc9032f5"},{"type":"text","text":"\n好问题。先看看现在面板里各个账号的状态：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ptsilwy6lwpw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/panel/strategy_performance_panel_latest.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\naccounts = d.get('accounts', d) if isinstance(d, dict) else d\nprint(f'账号总数: {len(accounts)}')\nfor a in accounts:\n    print(f'  {a.get(\\\"name\\\", a.get(\\\"account_id\\\", \\\"?\\\"))}')\n    print(f'    signal_date: {a.get(\\\"signal_date\\\", \\\"?\\\")}')\n    print(f'    status: {a.get(\\\"status\\\", \\\"?\\\")}')\n    print(f'    pnl_pct: {a.get(\\\"pnl_pct\\\", a.get(\\\"total_return\\\", \\\"?\\\"))}')\n    print()\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":133,"output":630,"cacheRead":35569,"cacheWrite":95528,"totalTokens":131860,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776178471073,"responseId":"062d8827d5ceb0a7e3399e29b6db9cee"}}
