{"type":"message","id":"09da121b","parentId":"f0326e47","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:56:13.958Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the picture more clearly:\n\n1. **Alpha55 纸盘**: signal_date=2026-04-07 (stale since 04-07!), return=0.00%. This is because the signal is stale and the account is in \"observe\" mode - not making new trades.\n\n2. **进取宽度独立盘 (breadth_aggressive)**: signal_date=2026-04-03, return=0.50%. This account is YELLOW because predictions stopped at 04-03. However, it had some positions from before that are still showing a small positive return.\n\n3. **严格样本外宽度盘 (breadth_strict_oos)**: signal_date=2026-03-30, return=-1.70%. \n\nThe breadth_strict_oos account went stale even earlier, about 15 days back. Looking at the returns, the offline accounts aren't actually outperforming the active ones - breadth_aggressive at 0.50% and alpha55 at 0.00% are both trailing behind the active accounts, with balanced at 5.64% and aggressive at 8.78%. The user might be seeing the breadth accounts in a different view or misunderstanding what they're showing. Looking at the active accounts, the returns vary dramatically—aggressive at 8.78% versus defensive at just 0.59%—which seems extreme for similar strategies, so there might be something off with how the predictions are being applied or the v4.3 account is using a completely different approach.\n\nThe real issue is likely about the breadth accounts. When predictions stopped updating after 04-03, those accounts couldn't rebalance into new positions. Since they were stuck holding what they had during the recent market recovery from 04-03 to 04-13, some of those frozen positions happened to rally, which could make it look like the stale accounts are performing better than they actually are. The aggressive account with the highest return at 8.78% is actually active, not offline, so the user's observation about offline accounts performing best doesn't quite match the data—unless they're referring to breadth_aggressive which gained 5.02% versus alpha55's 0.00%, though breadth_strict_oos is down 1.70%. I'm trying to figure out if there's a display issue in the HTML showing the wrong status, or if I'm misunderstanding which accounts are actually offline versus active.","thinkingSignature":"b6e16b8af7dcac45b3df5ad39a02a4aaddfafb7c9c216eb3b8642fb658cd44a7"},{"type":"text","text":"看到数据了。让我检查面板 HTML 看看实际展示：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_81yfenjt74rs_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/strategy_performance_panel_latest.* 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":100064,"output":574,"cacheRead":35569,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":136207,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776178552368,"responseId":"062d88784020cda469f8ed587052052c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c56d1299","parentId":"09da121b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:56:14.103Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_81yfenjt74rs_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"-rw-r--r--  1 ling  staff  31954 Apr 14 16:47 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/strategy_performance_panel_latest.html\n-rw-r--r--  1 ling  staff  18525 Apr 14 16:47 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/strategy_performance_panel_latest.json"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":37,"aggregated":"-rw-r--r--  1 ling  staff  31954 Apr 14 16:47 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/strategy_performance_panel_latest.html\n-rw-r--r--  1 ling  staff  18525 Apr 14 16:47 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/strategy_performance_panel_latest.json","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776178574085}}
{"type":"message","id":"b6705773","parentId":"c56d1299","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:56:26.604Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The panel HTML was generated at 16:47 today (April 14). Let me check what's in the HTML to see the actual display.\n\nActually, the user asked \"为什么要下线的纸盘收益却最好？\". Let me think about this more carefully.\n\nLooking at the data again:\n- breadth_aggressive (YELLOW): 0.50% total return (signal from 04-03, today is 04-14, 11 days stale)\n- alpha55 (YELLOW): 0.00% total return (signal from 04-07)\n- balanced (GREEN): 5.64%\n- aggressive (GREEN): 8.78%\n\n\n- breadth_strict_oos (YELLOW): -1.70%\n- exit_dual (YELLOW): -3.66%\n\nSo the breadth_aggressive account with its 0.50% return is actually outperforming all the YELLOW accounts and even the GREEN defensive account at 0.59%, but still lagging behind balanced and aggressive. The core issue is that this breadth account is frozen—it's holding stale positions from 11 days ago when the market was already declining.\n\nBut wait, the user said \"下线的纸盘收益却最好\" (offline paper trading accounts have the best returns), yet balanced and aggressive are both active and showing higher returns. Maybe the panel HTML is displaying these accounts differently than what I'm seeing in the JSON, or perhaps they're looking at something other than the raw percentage returns.\n\nI should check the cron scripts to understand how breadth accounts execute trades and whether the JSON data actually matches what's being rendered in the HTML report.","thinkingSignature":"b2d8dafc6683877efca682f4fe57241329fbac46a18e87736843da41030efb2b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8f1pq315ypt8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -l \"breadth_aggressive\\|breadth_strict\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/cron_breadth*.sh 2>/dev/null | head -3\necho \"---\"\ncat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/cron_breadth_paper_trading.sh 2>/dev/null | head -50"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":100760,"output":454,"cacheRead":35569,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":136783,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776178574104,"responseId":"062d888e0baa4f5bf2657125ceff327c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"06ac7042","parentId":"b6705773","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:56:26.722Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8f1pq315ypt8_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/cron_breadth_paper_trading.sh\n/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/cron_breadth_strict_oos_paper.sh\n---\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\ncd \"$ROOT\"\n\n# 非交易日跳过（qt.gtimg.cn 公开数据用 http 避免 Python 3.14 SSL 验证问题）\nMKT_DATE=$(python3 -c \"\nimport urllib.request, datetime\ntry:\n    req = urllib.request.Request('http://qt.gtimg.cn/q=sh000001', headers={'User-Agent':'Mozilla/5.0'})\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=5) as r:\n        c = r.read().decode('gbk', errors='replace')\n    for line in c.split(';'):\n        parts = line.split('~')\n        if len(parts) > 30:\n            mkt = parts[30].strip()[:8]\n            today = datetime.datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d')\n            if mkt != today:\n                exit(1)\n            exit(0)\n    exit(1)\nexcept:\n    exit(0)  # 网络异常时走cron 1-5兜底\n\" 2>/dev/null)\nif (($? != 0)); then\n    echo \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')] 非 A 股交易日，跳过 breadth_aggressive_paper\"\n    exit 0\nfi\n\nPYRUN=\"$ROOT/scripts/cron_python.sh\"\n\"$PYRUN\" --runtime-only\n\n\"$PYRUN\" scripts/run_breadth_paper_trading.py"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":32,"aggregated":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/cron_breadth_paper_trading.sh\n/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/cron_breadth_strict_oos_paper.sh\n---\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\ncd \"$ROOT\"\n\n# 非交易日跳过（qt.gtimg.cn 公开数据用 http 避免 Python 3.14 SSL 验证问题）\nMKT_DATE=$(python3 -c \"\nimport urllib.request, datetime\ntry:\n    req = urllib.request.Request('http://qt.gtimg.cn/q=sh000001', headers={'User-Agent':'Mozilla/5.0'})\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=5) as r:\n        c = r.read().decode('gbk', errors='replace')\n    for line in c.split(';'):\n        parts = line.split('~')\n        if len(parts) > 30:\n            mkt = parts[30].strip()[:8]\n            today = datetime.datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d')\n            if mkt != today:\n                exit(1)\n            exit(0)\n    exit(1)\nexcept:\n    exit(0)  # 网络异常时走cron 1-5兜底\n\" 2>/dev/null)\nif (($? != 0)); then\n    echo \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')] 非 A 股交易日，跳过 breadth_aggressive_paper\"\n    exit 0\nfi\n\nPYRUN=\"$ROOT/scripts/cron_python.sh\"\n\"$PYRUN\" --runtime-only\n\n\"$PYRUN\" scripts/run_breadth_paper_trading.py","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776178586710}}
{"type":"message","id":"60af1b33","parentId":"06ac7042","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:56:39.829Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the structure. The breadth cron scripts run the `run_breadth_paper_trading.py` script via `cron_python.sh`. \n\nThe core question: why does the breadth_aggressive account (which is STALE/offline) show good returns (0.50% which is close to or better than some active accounts)?\n\nLet me think about this:\n\n1. The breadth_aggressive account uses `signal_stale_hold` mode when the signal is stale - it holds existing positions rather than selling\n2. The signal_date is 2026-04-03, which means the last signal generation was for 2026-04-03\n\n\n3. The prediction file is stuck at 04-03, so when the cron script tries to run, it fails to generate new signals because there's no data beyond that date\n4. The account is essentially frozen in time with whatever positions it held on 04-03\n5. Those positions might have gained value during the subsequent market recovery (清明后市场反弹), which explains why the returns look decent despite being offline\n\nBut the user said the offline accounts show the \"best\" returns, which doesn't align with what I'm seeing—breadth_aggressive is only at 0.50%, much lower than balanced (5.64%) or aggressive (8.78%). Unless they're comparing against the worse YELLOW accounts like exit_dual (-3.66%) or breadth_strict_oos (-1.70%), where 0.50% would indeed be the best among the offline ones. The real question is what happens when the cron script tries to generate signals but finds no data—does it exit cleanly or leave the account in a broken state?","thinkingSignature":"8c74b88584078f0a2cbb0869da6d1d8f13b7cfe29da56aa26ea8d3b223cd4b29"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hito2z9x47j7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_breadth_paper_trading.py 2>/dev/null | head -60"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":101615,"output":416,"cacheRead":35569,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":137600,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776178586723,"responseId":"062d889ac1d900d3b4fe97e5ece8ed55"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ffb17f7a","parentId":"60af1b33","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:56:39.939Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hito2z9x47j7_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\n宽度策略模拟盘\n- 默认参数仍兼容旧版进取盘\n- 支持通过命令行覆写参数，生成严格样本外版本的独立模拟盘\n\"\"\"\nimport sys, os\nsys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(__file__))\n\nimport multiprocessing as mp\nmp.freeze_support()\n\nimport pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\nimport json\nimport argparse\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nDATA_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"data\" / \"ml_dataset_full\"\nPREDICTIONS_PATH = DATA_DIR / \"ml_predictions.csv\"\nLIVE_PREDICTIONS_PATH = DATA_DIR / \"ml_predictions_live_latest.csv\"\nFEATURES_PATH = DATA_DIR / \"ml_features_full.csv\"\nMAX_SIGNAL_LAG_DAYS = 2\nTODAY_STR = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d\")\nTODAY_ISO = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n\n\ndef append_history_records(summary: dict, slug: str) -> dict:\n    csv_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"{slug}_daily_history.csv\"\n    jsonl_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"{slug}_daily_history.jsonl\"\n    nav_history = summary.get(\"nav_history\", []) or []\n    compact_history: list[dict] = []\n    seen_markers: set[tuple[str, float, float]] = set()\n    for item in nav_history:\n        nav = round(float(item.get(\"nav\", 0.0)), 6)\n        cash = round(float(item.get(\"cash\", summary.get(\"cash\", 0.0))), 2)\n        marker = (str(item.get(\"date\") or summary.get(\"signal_date\")), nav, cash)\n        if marker in seen_markers:\n            continue\n        seen_markers.add(marker)\n        compact_history.append(item)\n    nav_history = compact_history\n    records: list[dict] = []\n    for idx, item in enumerate(nav_history):\n        nav = round(float(item.get(\"nav\", 0.0)), 6)\n        cash = round(float(item.get(\"cash\", summary.get(\"cash\", 0.0))), 2)\n        total_value = round(nav * float(summary.get(\"paper_capital\", 0.0)), 2)\n        market_value = round(total_value - cash, 2)\n        records.append(\n            {\n                \"generated_at\": f\"{summary.get('generated_at')}#{idx+1}\",\n                \"signal_date\": item.get(\"date\") or summary.get(\"signal_date\"),\n                \"nav\": nav,\n                \"total_value\": total_value,\n                \"cash\": cash,\n                \"market_value\": market_value,\n                \"position_count\": int(summary.get(\"position_count\", 0) or 0),"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":40,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\n宽度策略模拟盘\n- 默认参数仍兼容旧版进取盘\n- 支持通过命令行覆写参数，生成严格样本外版本的独立模拟盘\n\"\"\"\nimport sys, os\nsys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(__file__))\n\nimport multiprocessing as mp\nmp.freeze_support()\n\nimport pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\nimport json\nimport argparse\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nDATA_DIR = PROJECT_ROOT / \"data\" / \"ml_dataset_full\"\nPREDICTIONS_PATH = DATA_DIR / \"ml_predictions.csv\"\nLIVE_PREDICTIONS_PATH = DATA_DIR / \"ml_predictions_live_latest.csv\"\nFEATURES_PATH = DATA_DIR / \"ml_features_full.csv\"\nMAX_SIGNAL_LAG_DAYS = 2\nTODAY_STR = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d\")\nTODAY_ISO = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n\n\ndef append_history_records(summary: dict, slug: str) -> dict:\n    csv_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"{slug}_daily_history.csv\"\n    jsonl_path = REPORT_DIR / f\"{slug}_daily_history.jsonl\"\n    nav_history = summary.get(\"nav_history\", []) or []\n    compact_history: list[dict] = []\n    seen_markers: set[tuple[str, float, float]] = set()\n    for item in nav_history:\n        nav = round(float(item.get(\"nav\", 0.0)), 6)\n        cash = round(float(item.get(\"cash\", summary.get(\"cash\", 0.0))), 2)\n        marker = (str(item.get(\"date\") or summary.get(\"signal_date\")), nav, cash)\n        if marker in seen_markers:\n            continue\n        seen_markers.add(marker)\n        compact_history.append(item)\n    nav_history = compact_history\n    records: list[dict] = []\n    for idx, item in enumerate(nav_history):\n        nav = round(float(item.get(\"nav\", 0.0)), 6)\n        cash = round(float(item.get(\"cash\", summary.get(\"cash\", 0.0))), 2)\n        total_value = round(nav * float(summary.get(\"paper_capital\", 0.0)), 2)\n        market_value = round(total_value - cash, 2)\n        records.append(\n            {\n                \"generated_at\": f\"{summary.get('generated_at')}#{idx+1}\",\n                \"signal_date\": item.get(\"date\") or summary.get(\"signal_date\"),\n                \"nav\": nav,\n                \"total_value\": total_value,\n                \"cash\": cash,\n                \"market_value\": market_value,\n                \"position_count\": int(summary.get(\"position_count\", 0) or 0),","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776178599926}}
