{"type":"message","id":"b4f31a10","parentId":"a4a4c94c","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:57:01.851Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see. The staleness check compares the signal_date (from the predictions file) against the feature_latest_date and the current date. \n\nLet me now understand the complete picture of why an offline account might show good returns. Let me look at the key question more carefully.\n\nThe user said \"下线的纸盘收益却最好\" (offline paper trading accounts show the best returns). \n\nLooking at the data:\n- breadth_aggressive (YELLOW, STALE since 04-03): 0.50% return\n- breadth_strict_oos (YELLOW, STALE since 03-30): -1.70% return\n\n\n- alpha55 (YELLOW, STALE since 04-07): 0.00% return\n- balanced (GREEN): 5.64%\n- aggressive (GREEN): 8.78%\n\nSo among the YELLOW accounts, breadth_aggressive is actually the best performer at 0.50%, even though it's offline and not rebalancing. The market rallied during the stale period from 04-03 to 04-14, and the positions breadth_aggressive happened to hold from its last signal on 04-03 benefited from that upswing.\n\nMeanwhile, alpha55 stayed in cash because its signal was already stale when the rally started, so it missed the gains entirely. The other accounts that continued trading got caught in wrong positions or sold at the wrong time. That's why the frozen account ended up outperforming the active ones.\n\nBut I'm noticing something odd in the performance data—the most recent entries show breadth_aggressive jumped to 5.02%, which is a significant jump from the 0.50% I was looking at. Let me trace through the dates more carefully to figure out when this spike happened and what triggered it.\n\nLooking at the current status (16:47 on 04-14), the JSON shows breadth_aggressive as YELLOW because predictions haven't been updated since 04-03. But this 5.02% return suggests the cron job actually ran on 04-14, which doesn't align with the staleness status. I need to check whether the cron job is still executing or if there's a discrepancy in how the data's being reported.","thinkingSignature":"3a50ca0739bee18ebd4856209c6f0dee43a9dd07730d42b1116e07af9ca0e9f1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y9lcu0ffsqrl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 查看最新 breadth cron 日志\nls -la /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/logs/cron_breadth* 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\ncat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/logs/cron_breadth_paper_trading.log 2>/dev/null | tail -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":103195,"output":551,"cacheRead":35569,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":139315,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776178606197,"responseId":"062d88aef3da8f35e02ae6583c4bcd46"}}
