{"type":"message","id":"7f008666","parentId":"11fa090e","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:57:29.944Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture. The breadth_aggressive paper trading account:\n\n1. Last traded on 2026-04-03 (清明日后第一个交易日)\n2. On 2026-04-14 morning, when the cron ran, it checked the predictions file and found it's stale (no data beyond 04-03)\n3. It entered \"signal_stale_hold\" mode - no new trades, holding existing positions\n4. The existing 8 positions happened to gain value from 04-03 to 04-14, resulting in +2.5% gain (净值 from 0.9801 to 1.0050)\n\n\n5. Meanwhile, active accounts like aggressive (8.78%) and balanced (5.64%) significantly outperformed due to continuous trading, so the user's perception of breadth_aggressive having the best returns seems misaligned with the actual performance data.\n\nLet me reconsider what the user is actually seeing. Maybe they're comparing breadth_aggressive's 5.02% against something else, or perhaps there's a different time window or metric being used in the HTML display that I'm not accounting for.\n\nI should ask them to clarify what specific metric or comparison they're looking at when they say \"offline paper trading accounts are showing the best returns\" - the numbers I have show balanced and aggressive both significantly outperforming breadth_aggressive, so there's a disconnect between what they're observing and what the data shows.\n\nActually, thinking about this differently - the breadth_aggressive account has 8 stocks with a +16.1% gain in one position (603949 雪龙集团), which means if it had been actively trading, it would have rebalanced and potentially missed those gains. The \"offline\" status means it's holding winners that would have been sold if the signal staleness check had triggered a sell. But this only makes sense if the user is comparing against accounts that sold those positions and didn't hold them - if everyone held the same stocks, everyone would have the same returns.\n\nThe real question is why the active accounts aren't showing these kinds of gains if they're supposedly rebalancing daily. Either they're holding different stocks entirely, or the active trading strategy is actually underperforming the frozen position strategy during this rally.","thinkingSignature":"7d8d52fc3a311f1cf3409393fb09922e770cb7baca47097d5452fc43a32b3ad7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x90dxwlfp129_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -80 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/logs/breadth_paper_trading_cron.log 2>/dev/null | head -50"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":105149,"output":525,"cacheRead":35569,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":141243,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776178633084,"responseId":"062d88c9bcb237219fc606fbddbdb77f"}}
