{"type":"message","id":"3fac4fcd","parentId":"265387da","timestamp":"2026-04-14T14:57:47.277Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the picture more clearly. Looking at the log from 04-03, the breadth account:\n- 持仓无变化 (no trades) - but this was by choice, not because of staleness\n- The positions had mixed results (some winning, some losing)\n- The account had 8 positions with some good performers like 雪龙集团 (+9.0%) and 天马科技 (+7.6%), and some losers like 喜临门 (-17.6%)\n- Total nav was 0.9801 on 04-03\n\nNow on 04-14 (11 days later), the nav is 1.0050. So it gained about +2.5% during the stale period. The market appears to have rallied from 04-03 to 04-14.\n \nLooking at the individual positions, 雪龙集团 surged from +9.0% to +16.1% and 天马科技 improved from +7.6% to +8.0%, while 喜临门 dropped from -17.6% to -17.6%.\n\nThe active trading accounts are performing significantly better—the aggressive strategy is up 8.78% and balanced is up 5.64%, both outpacing the stale account's 0.50% return. But I'm realizing the user might be looking at the breadth account's total return since inception at 5.02% rather than just the recent performance, which would make it competitive with the other strategies. So the 5.02% in the HTML represents the total return since inception, while the log's 1.0050 is the current NAV—and there's a discrepancy where the log shows 0.50% recent return versus the 5.02% shown in the HTML.\n\nLet me trace through the dates in the log: it goes from 2026-04-03 (0.9801) through 2026-04-09, 04-10, and 04-13, with the latest entry showing today's NAV of 1.0050. The total return since inception would be 5.02%, which matches the HTML display. But I need to verify what the inception date actually was to understand if this performance is genuinely competitive or if there's still a timing issue I'm missing.","thinkingSignature":"bb881d5fdb8f731e34e529cd717b779a79e2d8cd1bfb49dd9a5a5ac9056f7854"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_