{"type":"message","id":"b82b0a51","parentId":"f9f74c6c","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:02:05.026Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log file doesn't exist. This means the cron at 16:30 didn't run yet. This is because we added the cron today (2026-04-14) and the cron daemon needs to reload. The log file path doesn't exist.\n\nActually wait - the cron was added today, and the `>> /path/to.log` means it creates the log file. But the file doesn't exist, which means the cron at 16:30 didn't execute. This could be because:\n1. The cron daemon wasn't restarted after we added the new cron entry\n2. It's running but logging elsewhere\n\nLet me check the overall situation more carefully. The user is asking about \"real-time\" paper trading. Let me re-read the cron setup:\n\n\nLooking at the actual cron entries, I see there's a breadth paper trading cron at 8:30 AM, an intraday paper trading cron at 1:30 PM that I wasn't aware of, and the daily qlib pipeline at 4:30 PM that we added today. The real issue is that the morning breadth cron ran today with stale predictions from April 3rd, and the afternoon cron never executed because we added it after 4:30 PM had already passed.\n\nFor actual real-time simulation, the user would need predictions updated before market open and a cron running during market hours to capture intraday execution signals. But there's a fundamental limitation: Tushare only provides daily data that gets populated at 4 PM, so there's no intra-day prediction refresh available. The user might be referring to a request they made this morning that I don't have full context for.\n\nLooking at what actually ran today versus what they wanted—the breadth cron did execute at 8:30 AM with the old predictions, generating a stale signal rather than real-time execution, while the intraday crons at 1:30 PM and 2:30 PM ran but apparently didn't capture anything. To get real-time paper trading working, we'd need to either ensure fresh predictions are available before the cron runs at 8:30 AM, or restructure when and how the signals get generated.\n\nThe core blocker is that predictions from Tushare only arrive at 4 PM the day before, so the morning cron at 8:30 AM has no choice but to work with stale data. I'm trying to figure out if this is a request I should already know about or if I need to ask for clarification on what specifically the user wants to automate. the crontab didn't take effect, probably because the cron daemon needs to reload. Let me check and fix that.","thinkingSignature":"4dda70bee9776a368f0bdc16f388b04f7e02ee68c6a971247263e912aa6e5f63"},{"type":"text","text":"16:30 的 cron 还没有执行（可能 cron 守护进程需要重载）。让我检查并确保整个流程明天能正常运行：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_76x6akfyabe5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 cron 守护进程状态\nps aux | grep crond | grep -v grep\necho \"---\"\n# 重载 cron\ncrontab -l 2>/dev/null | head -3\necho \"---\"\n# 确保 cron 服务在运行\nsudo launchctl list | grep cron 2>/dev/null || echo \"checking cron service\"\nlaunchctl load -w /System/Library/LaunchDaemons/com.vix.cron.plist 2>/dev/null && echo \"cron loaded\" || echo \"cron not available via launchctl\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109469,"output":689,"cacheRead":35569,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":145727,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776178903626,"responseId":"062d89d7237dfe92f27ff4b1a8a6a670"}}
