{"type":"message","id":"bff04664","parentId":"660370ef","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:02:14.998Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cron is loaded. The issue might be that the new cron entry wasn't picked up. Let me try to reload cron differently. Actually, `launchctl load` said \"cron loaded\" without needing sudo, which means it succeeded.\n\nBut the daily_qlib_pipeline.log doesn't exist. Let me check if the cron entry is actually in the crontab.","thinkingSignature":"482a01ea4c113148abb5d144977600e13ed12e7bb2e129364e950bbcacf58b83"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_es48ksz5soo3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 确认 daily_qlib_pipeline cron 是否在 crontab 中\ncrontab -l 2>/dev/null | grep qlib\necho \"---\"\n# 手动重载 cron\ncrontab -l | sed 's/^/ /' | tr '\\n' '\\0' | xargs -0 echo 2>/dev/null | grep \"qlib_pipeline\"\necho \"---\"\n# 检查 cron 是否真的在执行（查看 cron 日志）\nlog show --predicate 'processImagePath contains \"cron\" && eventMessage contains \"2026-04-14 16\"' --maxEntries 10 2>/dev/null | tail -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":110344,"output":238,"cacheRead":35569,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":146151,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776178925227,"responseId":"062d89ed0dfff434cb7e6e8e970ddc62"}}
