{"type":"message","id":"67f1b8cd","parentId":"13882514","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:02:58.554Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The 13:30 and 14:30 cron ran but the log went to `paper_profiles_cron.log`. And it says the predictions are being used. Let me check the paper profiles cron logs to see if they actually ran today.\n\nWait - the `paper_profiles_cron.log` shows it's using `paper_profiles_v1` script (at 08:25). But there's also the `run_paper_trading_profiles_auto_v1.sh` at 13:30 and 14:30. Those write to the SAME log file `paper_profiles_cron.log`. But the log only shows 08:25 entries.\n\n\nThe 13:30 and 14:30 entries didn't appear in the log, which is strange since the cron should have executed them. I'm wondering if the issue is that the breadth cron runs at 08:30 before market open and depends on fresh predictions, but since the predictions were stale at that time, it couldn't generate anything. The real question is whether the cron actually fired at 13:30 and 14:30 but failed silently, or if it didn't run at all. The cron logs only show 08:25 entries for paper_profiles_v1, not the expected 13:30 and 14:30 runs that should be there. The timing doesn't add up—the 13:30 and 14:30 intraday crons should have logged their activity, but the log only shows entries from 08:25 on 04-14 and 04-10, which suggests those later cron jobs either didn't run or their output went somewhere else entirely. I should verify whether those timestamps actually belong to the paper profiles cron or if I'm looking at the wrong log file.","thinkingSignature":"a8d70234cdd8dba3c48697dff348b0cc28bd461f437168337cc784f80017e8dc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cbca8fq4afhk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查日内 cron 是否实际运行了\ngrep \"2026-04-14 13\\|2026-04-14 14\\|PAPER_PROFILE\" \\\n  /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/logs/paper_profiles_cron.log 2>/dev/null | head -10\necho \"---\"\n# 搜索所有日志文件中的 13:30 和 14:30 执行记录\ngrep -r \"2026-04-14