{"type":"message","id":"00ea8be7","parentId":"78e9200d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:05:27.626Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The script failed with \"stale_price_source: market_trade_date=20260410 lag_days=4 target=20260414\". This means the price source data (`a_stock_history.csv`) is stuck at 04-10, not 04-13. That's why the intraday crons didn't produce valid output - the data is stale.The issue:1. `a_stock_history.csv` is at 04-10\n2. The script checks if the price data is current (needs 04-14 for today's trading)\n3. Since it's 4 days behind, it fails\n\nBut wait - we have `tushare_raw/daily_20260414.csv` (today's data). The `a_stock_history.csv` was probably generated from a different source.\n\n\nThe core problem is that the price data feed is lagging 4 days behind where it needs to be for the intraday cron to run successfully. The file was built from Tushare daily updates, but those updates haven't kept pace with the current date.\n\nI could either update `a_stock_history.csv` with the latest Tushare data to match the current date, or bypass the staleness check in the script itself. Since the script already failed gracefully, I should focus on what the user actually needs - a real-time paper trading capability that can run the next trading day with current data. The priority is ensuring the 08:30 morning cron has fresh predictions and the intraday crons at 13:30 and 14:30 have the necessary data to work properly.\n\nNow I'm looking at the morning breadth cron specifically, since that's what actually handles the paper trading signals. It's currently pointing to stale predictions from April 3rd when the market's been trading through April 14th, so it's likely outputting outdated signals rather than executing trades. The cron logs should clarify what it's actually producing, but based on the timestamps, it probably ran with the old data instead of today's fresh information.\n\nThe real issue is that I fixed the predictions file at 9 PM tonight, so the morning cron won't pick them up. The next opportunity is tomorrow at 08:30, assuming the 16:30 cron today actually runs and updates the data. The predictions file being referenced is from the ml_dataset_full directory, which might be a different version than what I just fixed in the main pipeline.","thinkingSignature":"be1b272ac38677f551dba78d63771bfc76fe82e987b195f96a52f9f9d09b2a99"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vddye95e0jkh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 查看 breadth cron 使用的是哪个 predictions 文件\ngrep \"predictions_live\\|ml_predictions\\|PREDICTION\" \\\n  /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_breadth_paper_trading.py 2>/dev/null | head -5\necho \"---\"\n# 检查 ml_dataset_full 目录的预测文件\nls -la /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/ml_dataset_full/ml_predictions*.csv 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\n# 对比我们的修复文件\nls -la /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/ml_predictions_live_latest.csv 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":114411,"output":665,"cacheRead":35569,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":150645,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776179106217,"responseId":"062d8aa253e4bb1ca4a72497e546507a"}}
