{"type":"message","id":"8d45e21d","parentId":"927297ad","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:07:35.361Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The breadth paper trading just ran and:- **Signal date**: 2026-04-13 ✅ (fresh!)- **Status**: 0 positions, was selling everything\n- **New NAV**: 0.9970 (was 1.0050)- **Signals**: SELL all 8 positions!The breadth paper trading received a SELL ALL signal because:1. The market breadth today (based on today's price data up to 04-13) was very weak2. All 8 positions are being liquidatedThis is actually good - it means the system is working. The signal is fresh (04-13), positions are being managed based on the breadth model.Now let me check: why did it sell everything? The signal freshness is now 04-13 (fresh!). Let me see the full output to understand why it sold.Wait - it says \"2026-04-14: 净值 1.0050\" and then \"2026-04-13: 净值 0.9970\". \n\nThe timeline is getting clearer - the 1.0050 valuation on 04-14 came from this morning's cron job running with stale predictions, but now with the fresh 04-13 signal processed, the NAV recalculated to 0.9970 based on the complete dataset available through 04-13.\n\nNow I should verify the broader paper trading systems and dashboard to confirm everything's aligned with the current predictions.","thinkingSignature":"32d58878492105d94e5d28fef1ce6afe91d43d65965daa39d57904e985dc825d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fupdt0f4b8ou_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 确认面板现在的状态\n/usr/bin/python3 -c \"\nimport pandas as pd\ndf = pd.read_csv('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/ml_dataset_full/ml_predictions_live_latest.csv')\nprint('预测文件: 最新', df['date'].max(), '共', len(df), '条')\n\" 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\n# 更新面板报告\ncd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && \\\n/usr/bin/python3 scripts/generate_dashboard_portal.py 2>&1 | tail -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages