{"type":"message","id":"d60fae56","parentId":"2cdbcc94","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:30:18.977Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me take a different approach. Instead of trying to debug the full intraday chain (which takes too long and uses too much memory), let me just check whether with the `PAPER_PROFILE_RUN_HEAVY_REPORTS=0` fix, the cron will work tomorrow. The cron itself is what matters for the user's request.\n\nBut I should still try to run the core components to at least confirm they work. Let me try running the intraday with a much shorter timeout to see if it starts properly.\n\nActually, let me just verify the cron fix is in place and the data is flowing correctly. The OOM issue with the intraday script is a known issue - the actual important thing for \"real-time simulation\" is that:\n\n\n1. The morning 8:30 cron runs breadth paper trading ✅ (works)\n2. The evening 16:30 cron runs the data pipeline ✅ (works)\n3. The intraday 13:30/14:30 crons run paper profiles with heavy reports skipped\n\nThe real problem is that `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py` is still loading too much data even without the heavy reports. I need to trace through that script to find where the memory bloat is happening, particularly in the `compose_` function and how it loads signals.\n\nLooking at the function flow, it reads base merged signals and profile buy signals from CSV files. But there's also `load_all_signal_sources_v2` which might be pulling in additional data that shouldn't be there.","thinkingSignature":"46507c9d8ce14948b927dfa0915dbdbe96ff245857a1e6cd9c8a7ff1f43c2686"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pevmrqkkwqe5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"def load_all_signal_sources\\|def compose_signals\\|def build.*signal\\|signal_source\" \\\n  /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/prepare_paper_orders_v1.py 2>/dev/null | head -10\necho \"---\"\ngrep -n \"daily_basi