{"type":"message","id":"6251695b","parentId":"c1e59ed5","timestamp":"2026-04-14T15:39:15.495Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The fix is in place. Now let me also check the P0-2 issue about the time order. Let me check the cron timestamps again.\n\nActually, I realized the issue: the GPT-5.4 said \"08:30 paper trading runs BEFORE 16:30 data pipeline\" is a problem. But this is actually correct by design - the paper trading at 08:30 uses the predictions generated at the PREVIOUS day's 16:30. That's the intended behavior.\n\nThe real question is: when the cron runs at 16:30 today and generates predictions for today (04-14), will the next morning's 08:30 breadth paper use those 04-14 predictions? Let me verify the cron order.\n\n\nThe 08:30 breadth paper cron should be using the most recent predictions from the 16:30 pipeline run, which would be the 04-14 predictions generated today. Let me trace through the actual cron execution to confirm this flow is working as intended.","thinkingSignature":"c19f24f16b924f1d30d827cf344968ccb1f3fd9d4a5e2911eb71f511ead2ee93"},{"type":"text","text":"\nPRED_END 硬编码已修复为动态读取日历。现在验证完整管道并解决 P0-2：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_niae8iyvonv7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 确认 pipeline 脚本的日期范围是动态的\ngrep \"PRED_END\\|end\\|start\" \\\n  /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_daily_qlib_pipeline.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54034,"output":304,"cacheRead":35391,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89729,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776181145876,"responseId":"062d929a34c0f3746a22ac35324ed5b7"}}
